title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large saucepan, cook squash until just tender; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, using half the cheese.
Put in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake 20 minutes more.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Lightly brown meat in fat; remove from pan.
Cook onion and garlic in fat until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except beans.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of beans.
Top with meat, then catsup mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until onions are soft.
Mix mashed potatoes (instant) according to directions on box.
Add soft onions and cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: paul bunyan breakfast
directions: Cut bacon
in
1-inch
strips
and fry in 10-inch Dutch oven until
almost
done.
Drain
most
of the grease, leaving enough to	brown
potatoes.
Add potatoes to bacon and brown. Scramble eggs on the lid of the oven, using some bacon grease. Add to potatoes and bacon.
Mix and serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in ovenproof baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until light brown on top.

title: chocolate fudge squares
directions: In top of double boiler over hot water, melt chocolate and butter or margarine.
In a bowl, beat eggs and sugar together until smooth.
Pour hot chocolate and butter mixture into beaten eggs and sugar, stirring well to keep mixture from curdling.
Pour mixture back into double boiler top.
Cook over heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in flour and nuts dredged in flour.
Stir well into chocolate mixture.

title: fish creole
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Combine onion, green pepper, garlic and 2 tablespoons water.
Cook, covered, until tender.
Add undrained tomatoes, parsley, bouillon, hot pepper sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes. Blend cornstarch and 3 tablespoons cold water; stir into tomato mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in fish.
Simmer, covered, 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican casserole (1)
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Season with salt, pepper, chili powder, and chilies.
Add soups and heat thoroughly.
Line casserole pan with broken tortillas.
Put 1/2 meat mixture over tortillas and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350°F for 30 min.

title: sweet crock pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and place in churn or crock.
Cover with brine water (1 cup salt/1 gallon water).
Cover with plate and brick to push all
cucumbers beneath brine water.
Let soak 14 days.
Wash, slice and place cucumbers back in churn with alum and water to cover.
Let soak 24 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Good over chicken.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip; blend well. Spoon into crust and chill for 4 hours.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and corn syrup to 242°, or until syrup spins a 6 to 8-inch thread.
Add butter and peanuts; cook slowly to 300°, stirring occasionally.

title: beef and potato bake
directions: Place potatoes in greased baking dish with 1 tablespoon onion. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt and parsley flakes.	Mix remaining ingredients
and	spread	evenly	over
potatoes. Decorate
top with
more ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: surprise jello
directions: Mix pretzels, melted butter and sugar well. Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass pan. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: *black cherry jello salad
directions: Bring to a boil the Coca-Cola and cherry juice.
Dissolve jello and cream cheese in this.
Cool and add cherries and nuts. Put into mold and chill until firm.

title: cabbage relish
directions: Grind cabbage, onions, tomatoes and peppers.
Sprinkle salt over and let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar, water, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over mixture.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pizza dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except pepperoni in slow cooker.
Top with pepperoni.
Cover.
Cook on low 2 hours.
Stir well before bringing to buffet.
Serve with snack crackers or pour over steamed cauliflower and broccoli.

title: angel food cake filling
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Fold in yogurt.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Slice cake into 3 layers.
Spread filling between layers.
Frost with whipped topping made with skim milk.

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Melt butter in 2 quart saucepan over medium heat, about 2 minutes.
Add
mushrooms,
onion
and green pepper; saute 5 minutes
or
until tender.	Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken soup, milk, pimientos and basil.
Arrange 4 noodles in greased 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Top
with
layers
of	1/2
of sauce, 1/2 cottage cheese, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 Cheddar cheese and 1/2 Parmesan cheese.
Add remaining noodles and repeat layers. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon and add to sugar mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Fill bread pans 1/2 full. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Yield: 3 large or 4 small loaves.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Add all in electric mixer bowl.
Beat until well mixed. Batter will
be
thick.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan that has been greased
and
floured.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until when tested
toothpick
comes out clean.
Top will crack.
Let cool before
removing
from pan.
Serve with ice cream or just plain.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix in mixer jar. Add blue cheese after mixing. Cheese stays chunky. Refrigerate. Makes 1 quart.

title: cheese and rice dish
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Chop up dried beef.
Stir all ingredients together.
(Add optional ingredients now.)
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Quick, easy and good!
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: spicy, crunchy chicken or turkey salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, Tabasco and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Serve on bread, in a sandwich or on crackers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Warm corn and sour cream in oven while mixing cornmeal mixture.

title: corned beef croquettes
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan, add the mashed potato and cream, and heat thoroughly.
Next, put in the meat, parsley and seasoning, and lastly, the beaten egg.

Spread the mixture on a plate and when cool shape into croquettes, either in the form of large corks or a cone; coat with beaten egg and bread crumbs, and fry golden brown in smoking-hot oil or Crisco.

title: cherry-pineapple cake(dump cake)
directions: Do not mix!
Layer in glass 9 x 13-inch dish in order given. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Beat egg, water and vinegar.
Add salt and shortening to flour and mix.
Then add egg mixture to flour mixture.
Makes two double-crust pies.

title: rhubarb custard bars
directions: Mix with pastry blender and press into a sprayed 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Melt margarine.
Add bread crumbs.
Mix.
Save juice from 1 can of clams.
Drain the other 2.
Mix clams, onion, pepper, Tabasco sauce
and bread crumbs together in casserole dish. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Serve hot on crackers.

title: easy toffee bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hollywood pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook until thick. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Pour into pie shell and cover with meringue. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in saucepan. Blend in milk. Add butter. Bring to rolling
boil.
Add vanilla.
Remove from heat. Serve over hot biscuits. Add additional butter to taste.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water; set aside.
Cream butter, brown sugar, white sugar and eggs together.
Combine baking soda, cinnamon, vanilla and all-purpose flour together.
Mix oatmeal and creamed mixture, then add flour mixture into wet mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beet pickles
directions: Bring to a boil.
Boil beets.
Peel off skin in cold water. Pack jars.
Fill with liquid.
Seal.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease well Bundt pan.
Put in half of nuts and rolls. Sprinkle with dry pudding over rolls.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and margarine.
Pour over rolls.
Add remaining nuts.
Fix the night before.
Put in cold oven the next morning (don't preheat oven). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert on plate immediately.

title: louisiana mud-bug pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl. Spread ingredients into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until lightly brown.
Let cool.

title: elderberry bran muffins
directions: Cover elderberries with boiling water and let soak 3 hours. Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Add bran and elderberries. Beat egg and mix with milk, molasses and margarine.
Add dry ingredients and mix only enough to dampen all dry ingredients. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Makes one dozen.

title: parmesan cheese fingers
directions: Blanch and chop almonds and saute in butter until golden.
Mix cheese, cream and parsley.
Add salt and pepper to taste, then spread on toast strips.
Sprinkle tops with almonds and put in hot oven to heat thoroughly.
Makes 12 canapes.

title: salad dressing pickles
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and let stand overnight in brine made of 1/2 cup salt to 3 quarts water.
Drain and rinse.
Slice thin or chop fine the onions.
Mix sugar, spices, flour and vinegar. Add cucumbers, onions and pimento.
Cook 10 minutes.
Pack while hot in sterilized jars and seal.

title: strawberry minute pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Pour boiling water over Jell-O.
Stir to dissolve.
Add frozen strawberries; stir to break berries apart. When mixture is partially set, pour into baked pie shell.
Chill to set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine until amber-colored.
Add consomme and rice.
Cook in baking dish at 325°, uncovered, about 50 minutes.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Using a large, long pan, cover bottom of pan by laying rolls out flat.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: apple butter muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, spice and salt.
Make a well in the center.
Combine egg, milk and applesauce and add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir until moist.
Spoon a rounded tablespoon batter into muffin cup.
Top each with a rounded teaspoon apple butter, then with the rest of the batter.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.
Makes 9 muffins.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add taco seasoning.
Mix together with remaining ingredients.
Before serving, add tortilla chips.

title: roasted peppers
directions: In a 2 1/2 quart casserole dish combine oil, garlic, anchovies, red pepper and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add peppers, stirring to coat. Cook, covered on High 14 to 16 minutes until peppers are soft, stirring twice during cooking.
Serve hot, warm or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix and boil the sugar, salad oil and vinegar.
When cool, add liquid to vegetables.

title: creamier fudge
directions: Blend creamer and hot water in 2-quart saucepan and add butter, sugar and salt.
Heat to boiling (start timing when mixture starts to bubble around pan edges).
Cook 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream, chocolate pieces and vanilla.
Stir vigorously 1 minute.
Pour into buttered 8 x 10-inch pan.
Cool in refrigerator and cut into squares.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Brown meat; pour off fat.
Add other ingredients, except cabbage.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cabbage.
Cover and cook until tender.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream shortening. Add sugar. Mix. Add tomato soup with baking soda already dissolved in it. Mix. Sift rest of ingredients together (except the raisins and nuts). If you don't feel like sifting (I never do), just mix the dry ingredients together gently. Add the dry ingredients to the mixture. Stir. Then stir in the raisins and nuts. Pour into a greased 8 x 8 or 9

x 9 square pan. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until cake is brown. Insert a toothpick in center to check for doneness. If pick comes out clean, cake is done. If toothpick is full of wet batter, let it bake a while longer.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, butter and 4 tablespoons sugar.
Press in 9 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Let cool.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender, until size of small peas.
Sprinkle water over mixture, while tossing quickly with fork, until particles stick together. Form into smooth ball.
For ease, roll pastry on Tupperware pastry cloth and wax paper.
Make 1 inch larger than pie pan.
Pat out air; crimp edges.
Prick entire crust thoroughly before baking. This prevents bubbles and excess shrinkage.
Bake in a hot oven (450°) for about 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 4 (9-inch) pie crusts.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix Velveeta cheese; grate Cheddar cheese.
Mix cream cheese. Mix all together.
Make into a roll and roll in chili powder.

title: hidden pear salad
directions: In a saucepan boil pear liquid; add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and cool at room temperature until syrupy.
Meanwhile puree pears in blender.
In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and lemon juice until smooth and creamy.
Add pureed pears and mix well.
Prepare whipped topping according to package directions.
Fold into pear mixture.
Fold in cool gelatin.
Pour into 4 1/2-cup greased mold.
Chill overnight.
Serve squares on lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Saute onions, bell pepper and celery in butter.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic salt and chili powder.
Cook slowly 30 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and cook about 5 minutes more.
Stir in bacon.
Serve on hot rice.

title: bean soup
directions: In a Dutch oven,
add
water,
onion
and
beans (rinse beans first).
Bring to
a
boil; simmer about 1 hour.
Remove onion. Add rest of
the
ingredients
and
cook until tender. Remove ham hock and let
cool; remove what meat you can.
Dice the meat and return to
the soup.
Serve with corn bread and a dash of hot sauce.

title: marble cheesecake
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust; set aside.
Combine cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, sour cream and 2 teaspoons vanilla in mixer bowl.
Add flour, 1 tablespoon at a time, blending well.
Combine cocoa and 1/4 cup sugar in small bowl.
Add oil, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 cup of cream cheese mixture; mix until well blended.
Spoon plain and chocolate mixture alternately into prepared crust, ending with dollops of chocolate on top.
Gently swirl with knife or spatula for marbled effect.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Without opening oven door, decrease temperature to 250° and continue to bake for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Let cheesecake remain in oven for 30 minutes more without opening door.
Remove from oven; cool 10 minutes.
Loosen cake from side of pan and remove from pan.
Cool completely; chill thoroughly.

title: grandma eva's chicken soup
directions: Put all ingredients in pot (except noodles).
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.
If desired, add noodles last 8 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine
and
mix
all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well. Bake in 2 well-greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool or eat while warm.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick melted margarine with graham cracker crumbs. Pat evenly over the bottom of pan only. Beat together eggs, remaining margarine and sugar; use electric mixer and beat no less than 15 minutes. Spread this mixture over the graham cracker crumbs. Cover with sliced bananas. Spread drained pineapple over bananas. Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts and cherries. Refrigerate for 4 or 5 hours or overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine flour, butter and milk in pan and cook until thick. Melt 1 stick butter and pour over cracker crumbs.
Put layer of each, squash, sauce and crackers in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Put in casserole dish in layers as listed and pour undiluted soup over.
Put foil on top or cover with lid.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until potatoes test done.
Serves 8.

title: curry chickens and cashews
directions: Slice chicken breast lengthwise into strips.
Place strips in casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and curry.
Pour over chicken.
Bake covered about half an hour at 350°.
Remove cover and sprinkle with cashews and bake another 15 minutes.
(Chopped green onions also cook nice.)
Serve with steamed rice.

title: squash tian
directions: Shake squash chunks in a bag of flour; shake off excess flour. Put into oiled or buttered shallow baking dish.
Scatter with cheese, minced garlic and pepper to taste.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Put into a preheated 400° oven.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes. Serve hot.

title: quick peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Arrange peaches in a square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix baking mix, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter with a fork. Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake until light brown, about 20 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In large mixer bowl, cream 1/2 cup butter with granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour alternately with milk.

title: german kuchen cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread half the batter in a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Spread pie filling over batter and spread rest of batter over filling.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°; if using glass dish, 325°.

title: macadamia nut cookies
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugars.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Add Macadamia nuts and chopped white chocolate.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly on cookie sheet.

title: omelet with bacon
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Prepare oven.
Reserve bacon.
Heat margarine in rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, in oven until melted.
Tilt dish to coat bottom.
Beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt in large bowl until blended.
Stir in onions.
Pour into dish.
Bake omelet mixture and bacon about 35 minutes or until eggs are set, but moist, and bacon is hot.
Arrange omelet on large platter with bacon.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook the ingredients except parsley until the chicken is done, then strain broth into pot.
Add parsley and bring to a boil, then add noodles.
Cook until noodles are done.

title: mango chutney cream cheese mold
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in food processor.
Pour into lightly oiled 3 to 4-cup mold and chill overnight.
Remove from mold and place chutney over and around.
Sprinkle coconut over mold and serve with assorted crackers.

title: pork chops with milk gravy
directions: Roll chops in mixture, coating well. Brown on both sides in 1 1/2 Tbsp. hot fat. Add 1 cup water, cover and cook slowly 30 minutes or until tender. Remove chops to a warm platter. Pour milk into skillet and heat until steaming hot, but do not allow to boil. Serve with chops.

title: lemon christmas cake
directions: Cream butter, adding sugar a little at a time.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add lemon extract and 3 cups of flour. Flour cherries and pineapple with remaining 3 cups of flour and mix with batter.
Beat egg whites until stiff (but not dry) and fold in.
Bake in tube pan (not Bundt pan) for 3 hours at 250°.

title: lite chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Arrange on a plate with tomatoes and lettuce or use for sandwiches.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook, bone and cut up chicken. Saute in oleo the green pepper, celery and onion, chopped. Place in large pan the chicken, broth, vegetables, soup and cheese (in chunks) and simmer very slowly 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Add eggs and olives (cut up) or jar of pimentos. If this mixture is runny, add flour and water thickening, so it is like medium cream sauce. About 30 minutes before serving, cook 1 pound spaghetti (sometimes long, sometimes elbow). Mix well together.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat pork chops with flour mixture, place in oblong baking dish.
Add potatoes, cut in half, around the meat.
Cover with water and cook about 1 hour or until done turning once.

title: tostadas
directions: Using tongs, immerse tortillas, one at a time, in hot shortening.
Turn once while cooking until light golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: fruit smoothies
directions: Add yogurt or other berries or fruit. Blend, pour and serve.

title: busy day enchiladas
directions: Brown
hamburger
meat	in
skillet
and add Ro-Tel and soup. Simmer until well blended.	Crumble Fritos in bottom of casserole dish
and
pour
soup
and meat mixture over Fritos. Add grated cheese
on	top.
Bake until cheese is melted in a 350° oven.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery

title: sad cake
directions: Mix well and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: blue ribbon cornsticks
directions: Combine dry ingredients; mix well.
Add egg, milk and oil; stir until smooth.
Place in a well-greased cast iron cornstick pan in a 425° oven for 3 minutes; then spoon batter 2/3 full into pans.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sprouts and fried rice salad
directions: Heat oil in wok or skillet.
Add cooked rice and ginger.
Stir constantly over medium heat until the rice is heated through. Transfer to a large mixing bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until lightly chilled.

title: circus peanut salad
directions: Stir gelatin and circus peanuts together in boiling water until gelatin is dissolved.
Let set until almost firm.
Fold in drained pineapple and whipped topping.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: penuche frosting
directions: Combine sugars with milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil slowly, stirring until sugars are completely dissolved.
Cover saucepan and boil slowly for 2 minutes.
Uncover and boil to soft ball stage (232°).
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool until 110°.
Beat until frosting loses its gloss.
Add hot water and continue until good spreading consistency.
Spread quickly on cake.

title: citrus chicken with dates
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Rub with garlic, rosemary and cinnamon (I roll in Shake 'n Bake mixed with onion soup mix).

Brown quickly in oil. Add 1/4 cup of cut dates and onions to skillet. Cook on low, covered, until chicken is tender. Combine pineapple juice with lemon and orange juice. Stir in cornstarch and add to skillet.
Boil and thicken slightly. Add pineapple and remaining dates.
Heat through.
Remove from heat. Add orange and lemon zest.
Serves 4.

title: finnish pancake(serves 4)
directions: Place all ingredients except butter in blender.
Blend and scrape sides.

title: *baked fish tava
directions: Saute onion in 3 tablespoons oil until soft but not brown, stirring often. Add chopped tomatoes, parsley, salt and pepper. Simmer together for 5 minutes.

title: pierogi(polish dish)
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs and water.
Add flour slowly. Continue to add flour till dough is a soft mass.
Turn out onto a floured board and knead till dough becomes smooth.
Wrap in plastic wrap and store in refrigerator no less than 30 minutes. Take out about 1/3 of dough at a time.
Roll out on floured board as thin as possible, then cut into 3 inch circles.
Do not reroll any leftover dough, it gets tough.
Put 1 tablespoon or more of your chosen filling, fold over and seal.
Repeat till you have all circles filled.
Drop Pierogi into lightly salted boiling water. Cook till Pierogi floats.
Lift out with slotted spoon.
Saute in melted butter till desired brownness.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients into a large bowl.
Lightly dust the raisins with flour.
(This keeps them from falling to the bottom of	the
muffins.)	Add the raisins, coconut, carrots, apples
and nuts;
stir well.	Add the eggs, oil and vanilla, stirring only until combined.

title: "sweeten the catch"
directions: The night before cooking, take fish, wash off and put in bowl of ice water that has cooking soda and salt. After soaking in the refrigerator overnight or longer, wash fish.
Pat dry and prepare either fried, broiled or poached.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large covered casserole.
Put in a 250° oven and forget it for 5 hours or until meat is tender.
It gets nice and brown and is delicious.

title: sauerbraten with gingersnap gravy and noodles(yield:  6 to 8 servings)
directions: Place meat in large bowl or crock.
Combine next 9 ingredients and pour over meat.
Place in refrigerator and marinate at least 48 hours (the longer you marinate, the spicier the meat).
Turn the meat occasionally.
The morning of the day you plan to serve the meat, remove from marinade and brown on all sides in hot fat or oil.
Add one cup of marinade mixture; cover and cook at 300° for 3 to 4 hours until tender.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar and beat.
Beat in eggs, stir in sifted dry ingredients and rolled oats.
Mixture will be crumbly. Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Add nuts if you wish.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Add onion and bell pepper; cook until wilted.
Add tomato sauce, brown sugar, garlic juice, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce; stir.
Add pork and beans; stir again.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Spread 1 package of crescent rolls in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix all other ingredients and spread on top of rolls.
Lay other package rolls on top to form crust.
Brush egg white over top rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: pineapple salad dressing
directions: Cook altogether until thick.
Thin with whipped cream when ready to serve.

title: asparagus italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray rectangular baking dish with nonstick spray; place asparagus in single layer in bottom of dish. Top with remaining ingredients in the order given.
Cover and bake 20 minutes or until asparagus is tender-crisp.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain juice from clams and pour over vegetables in medium saucepan.
Add salt and enough water to cover.
Simmer, covered, over medium heat until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let cool.
Beat Crisco, white sugar, brown sugar and eggs well and add to oatmeal mixture. Stir in flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add to first mixture along with the chopped nuts.
Bake in long pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Mix margarine, coconut and dry cake mix together and press into bottom and slightly up the sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Cream pumpkin and sugar. Beat in eggs. Add the rest of the ingredients. In separate small bowl, combine the following:

title: fried rice
directions: Cook bacon and remove from pan.
Brown onions, peppers, bean sprouts and peas.
Add rice and mix.
Add soy sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir until rice is heated.

title: crab meat party dip
directions: Form cream cheese into a ball.
Mix and heat the drained crab meat with the chili sauce.
Pour over the cheese ball.
Use knife to spread sauce and cheese on crackers.
Good on Ritz or Triscuits.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend eggs, one at a time. Stir in flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture.
Chill several hours.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Shape into balls about 1 inch in size.
Place in a microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover loosely and microwave on High for 3 minutes. Rearrange meatballs.
Microwave another 6 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Drain.
Makes about 24.
Serve with spaghetti and sauce.

title: lye hominy
directions: Dissolve the lye in boiling water
using iron kettle or enameled ware.
Add corn.
Boil several minutes or until hulls loosen.
Rinse corn through several changes of water to remove lye.

title: daisy eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks; set whites aside. In a small bowl, mix together yolks, mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Spoon into a small empty butter tub lined with plastic wrap to mold.
Chill one hour, then remove and turn onto serving platter center.
Arrange egg whites around for petals.

title: fried apples
directions: Heat grease or butter in skillet.
Add apples, sugar and water. Cover and fry over low heat until tender.

title: chocolate dream
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Remove cake from oven and poke holes in cake.
Pour milk and caramel topping over cake.
Cool.
Spread Cool Whip over top of cake.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients in a heavy saucepan and cook 3 minutes until mixture pulls away from edge of pan.
Cool and knead.
Store in airtight container.
Do not eat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, including cheese.
Put in a greased casserole.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle plentifully on top.
Drizzle with plenty of melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Chill in refrigerator about 24 hours.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Add almonds; toss with dressing and serve.

title: tortellini with pesto
directions: In a food processor, combine the basil and garlic to a coarse puree. Add cheese and blend.
While the motor is running, add olive oil in a thin steady stream through the feed tube (if you do not have a feed tube, just add the oil in small amounts and process mixture in between).
Add the pine nuts and blend the mixture until smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Boil the tortellini.
When done, drain.
Mix pesto sauce into tortellini.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Toss all together and let set at least 1 hour before serving.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Parboil squash in salt water about 5 minutes or until tender. Cool.
Scoop out squash, leaving a boat.
Take pulp and add butter, salt, seasoned pepper and onion.
Cook until done.	Spoon mixture back into squash boats.
Cover with buttered breadcrumbs and cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven until cheese is melted and topping is brown (about 25 to 30 minutes).

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate, 9 x 1 1/2-inch or 10 x 1/2-inch.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2 1/2 quart casserole dish. Beat egg yolks.
Add creamed corn, milk, oil, shredded cheese and muffin mix.
Beat egg whites and fold into other mixture.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
If it gets too brown, turn oven down to 350° for last 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: fish house tea
directions: Combine in a large bowl orange juice, lemonade and limeade; set aside.
Steep tea bags in boiling water; add sugar, tap water and gin.
Add tea to orange juice mixture.
Freeze.
To serve mix 1/2 slushy tea with 1/2 ginger ale.

title: mississippi roundsteak sandwich
directions: Place skillet on eye of stove.
Let oil get hot.
Slit bologna 3 times around to keep from curling.
Fry bologna and put on bread.
Add garnish of your choice.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix altogether except morsels and wax and drop by teaspoons on tray on wax paper.
(Chill until firm.)
After set, melt 2 packages semi-sweet morsels and 2 sticks of wax over low heat.
Dip candy in chocolate with toothpick until it stops dripping.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain juice from 4 cans of beans and discard juice (set beans aside).
In large skillet, mix onions, brown sugar, Karo syrup, dry mustard, onion powder, margarine and salt and pepper.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Mix with beans.
Bake in 275° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.
Sprinkle bacon on top and then serve.
Will serve 40.

title: dill pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over pretzels.
Bake at 225° for 10 minutes on each side.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Cook until dissolved the water, sugar and cream of tartar. Break 15 crackers into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle on 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg.

title: bar-b-cups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground chuck.
Add onion, pepper and barbecue sauce.
Let this simmer while you make the cups. Open biscuits; press each biscuit into muffin pan bottom and up sides to form a cup.
Fill with meat mixture; top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: butter pecan pound cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese for 2 minutes.
Gradually add sugar; beat 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until yellow disappears.
Gradually add flour; mix at low speed.
Stir in pecans, flavoring and morsels.
Spoon batter into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, pimientos, green pepper and black pepper. Place over low heat.
Add cheese and heat until melted.
Mix macaroni and tuna in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add cheese sauce and bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries finely with part of orange skin.
Dissolve gelatin and sugar in water.
Add cranberries and remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Chill, stirring occasionally until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add baking soda, baking powder, flavorings and sour cream.
Add eggs, 2 at a time, with flour, alternately.
Beat well after each addition.
Bake in tube pan (that is greased and floured) at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open oven door until cake is done.
Do not cut cake until next day.

title: foolproof fudge frosting
directions: Mix sugar, salt, vanilla, melted oleo and milk in mixing bowl; blend well. Melt chocolate chips in microwave or double boiler and add quickly to sugar. Beat hard until frosting begins to thicken and loses shiny look; pour on cake and spread quickly.

title: vanilla cream pie(chocolate, or coconut, or banana or butterscotch)
directions: Prepare pie crust by sprinkling 1 teaspoon flour on one side and put that side down in the pie plate.
Refrigerate remaining crust for later use.

title: beer batter
directions: Combine dry ingredients, beer, egg and vegetable oil in container of electric blender; process until smooth.
Coat suggested food with flour.
Dip into batter with tongs or fork, allowing excess batter to drip into bowl; fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain.

title: red rice
directions: Fry bacon dry.
Remove from pan.
Cook the onions tender.
Add washed rice, tomatoes, seasonings and crumbled bacon.
Cook on top of stove 10 minutes.
Pour in casserole.
Cover tightly.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour, stirring with fork a couple of times.

title: cheese cake cupcakes
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Place vanilla wafers, upside-down in muffin pans.
Pour cream cheese mixture 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Top with fruit pie filling.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix cooked carrots, onion, cheese and can of celery soup, diluted with 1/3 cup milk.
Put into a 2-quart casserole.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Layer chopped pecans and coconut in pan.
Mix cake mix as package directs.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and melted oleo. Pour over cake.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Do not overcook, may not look done.

title: can do quick sweet dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in large mixer bowl.
Add buttermilk, eggs, 2 1/2 cups flour, margarine, sugar, baking powder and salt. Blend on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping sides of bowl.
Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Stir in remaining flour.
Knead for 5 minutes or about 200 turns on lightly floured board.
Shape as desired.
Let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour. (Dough is ready to bake if slight dent remains when touched.) Bake at 350°.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Take skin off chicken and rinse meat.
Roll chicken in bread crumb mixture. Arrange in 2-quart shallow baking dish already prepared with melted margarine or nonstick spray.
Bake for 20 minutes, then turn chicken and bake 20 minutes.

title: gumdrop fruitcake
directions: Cut fruit and gumdrops in small pieces.
Dredge in flour and coconut.
Add nuts and condensed milk.
Mix well and place in 9 x 5-inch bread pan with waxed paper lining in bottom.
Bake at 250° about 1 hour or until lightly browned.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and dice.
Boil in salt water until tender, not mushy.
Cool and add celery, onion, eggs, pickle and tomatoes. Mix in mayonnaise.
Let set for 2 or 3 hours for best flavor.

title: cinnamon pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into pie shell. Bake 30 minutes.

title: spicy macaroni bake
directions: In skillet, brown sausage; drain.
Add celery and cook lightly. Add tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In 1 1/2-quart baking dish, layer half the macaroni, half the meat and half the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: spicy milk tea
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add cinnamon, cloves and ginger. Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add tea and steep for a few minutes.
Add milk.
Bring to boil again.
Remove from heat. Strain into tea pot.
Serve with a sprinkle of cardamom and a bit of honey.

title: squash bread
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients.
Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix. Add dry ingredients.
Mix until blended.
Stir in squash, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: peach cobbler
directions: You may use fresh or canned peaches, cherries, etc.

title: rum raisin sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine the pie filling and rum.
Serve warm or cold over ice cream, fruit or cake.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and run cold water over macaroni, draining thoroughly.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar, then mix all ingredients including cooled macaroni and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Serves 8.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in 1 quart of water until tender. Mash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour entire mixture into crock-pot.
Simmer for an hour or two.
Sure good!

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in covered bowl.
Place in refrigerator.
Will keep several days.

title: riced potatoes au gratin
directions: Add butter, seasonings and eggs to hot riced potatoes.
Mix together and mound in baking dish.
Cover with cheese and crumbs. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: protein potassium power blend
directions: Mix in blender until smooth.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add onions and ground beef. Cook until golden brown. Drain. In separate bowl, add remaining ingredients. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish (sprayed with Pam). Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. This can be made the day before and baked when ready.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and baking powder together 2 to 3 times.
Add nuts. Add flour mixture to sugar mixture.
Add carrots, a small amount at a time.
Bake for 30 minutes in layers at 350°.

title: grilled turkey breast
directions: Pour dressing over halved turkey breast; refrigerate and marinate overnight.
Remove meat from marinade and use toothpicks to pin 2 strips of bacon to each side of each half.
Grill over charcoal, turning frequently, long enough to cook thoroughly but not long enough to dry out the meat.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In a large pan, bring milk, rice, butter and salt to a boil, stirring with a fork.
Put lid on and turn on low until rice is done (about 30 minutes).
In a small bowl, beat egg, sugar, cinnamon and vanilla together.
Stir in with rice until thick and creamy like pudding.
Let cool 30 minutes.
Pour into casserole. Cover to stay creamy.
Chill.
Sprinkle with cinnamon when served.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, margarine and oil.
Add flour, bananas and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken
directions: 1. Spray 13 x 9 pan with Pam. Tear tortillas up and line bottom. Layer chopped chicken over tortillas. Mix
tomatoes, chilies, onion, green pepper, and salt (Cut
up tomatoes).
2. Pour tomato mixture over chicken. Layer cheese over it.
Mix soups together and warm in microwave. Spread soups
over cheese.
3. Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes, uncovered.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Simmer for 1 hour. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Freezes well.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease (not oil) and lightly flour bottom of an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In a large saucepan, melt margarine and chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Blend in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set in center.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: chocolate cookie pudding
directions: Whisk together pudding mix and milk for 2 minutes. Cover and chill 5 minutes. Stir together cream cheese and topping, blending well. Place 1 cup cookies on bottom of an 8-cup bowl. Spread 1/2 of cream cheese mixture over cookies; sprinkle with 1/2 of the pecans. Spread pudding evenly over top. Spread remaining cream cheese over pudding. Sprinkle with remaining cookies and pecans. Chill until ready to serve.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir until blended; set aside.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil; cool to warm.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well and knead.
Place in a well-greased bowl. Cover with aluminum foil.
Keep in refrigerator and take out as needed.
Roll into balls, about the size of a walnut, put in well-greased muffin pan and let rise.
Bake in oven at 350° to 400° until brown.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: party punch
directions: Mix and serve with orange slices or freeze and thaw for slush.

title: four cup salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix gently all ingredients and chill.

title: little applesauce doughnut holes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop batter into hot oil by teaspoon.
Doughnuts will turn over by themselves and will be done in about 1 minute.

title: recipe for browned rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add raw rice, then add beef consomme and slivered almonds.
Bake in covered casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Tasty, but simple.

title: delicious cheese ball
directions: Let the cream cheese come to room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients except beef.
Shape into a ball.
Roll into the chopped beef.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Beat until well blended.
Cook over medium heat, stir constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Cook 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Serve over hot buttered biscuits.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Slice potatoes and onion in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour soup over top.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with ground beef.
Cover and cook.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix in a medium bowl with electric mixer on medium speed; beat cheese with margarine and vanilla until creamy.
Add confectioners sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: mock prime rib
directions: Place roast in glass pan.
Rub in salt, pepper and any seasonings you prefer.
Place, uncovered, in 375° preheated oven for 1 hour.
(Do this mid-afternoon.)
After 1 hour, turn off oven but do not open oven door.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease deep pie dish and pour in mixture.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cornflake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and bring to boil.
Add peanut butter and stir well.
Add cornflakes, press in pan and cut.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine ham, bread crumbs, egg, milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Roll into small balls.
Place in pan.
Mix brown sugar, mustard, vinegar, pineapple and juice.
Pour over balls in pan. Bake 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Good to use up leftover ham.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Fold in flour.
Add vanilla.
Beat.
Bake at 300° to 325° in a greased and floured pan for 1 1/2 hours, or until done.

title: hot snack
directions: Grind together first four ingredients; add mayonnaise.
Chill. Spread on snack rye.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: shrimp with eggs
directions: Heat pan with oil.
Add garlic, celery and onion.
After draining shrimp, mix shrimp with green onions, oyster sauce, sugar and garlic salt.
Add to pan and stir-fry fast.
Add eggs.
Cook until well done.

title: cooked cabbage and vegetables(low-fat)
directions: Steam or boil halved or quartered potatoes, carrots and onions until tender, about 1 hour.
While vegetables are cooking, heat 1 1/4 cups milk in a large nonstick skillet.
Add Gifford's Basic Spice and lemon juice, if desired.
Add cabbage; cover and simmer about 3 minutes.
Whisk flour into remaining 1/4 cup milk until it is smooth.
Season.
Add to cooked cabbage.
Boil and stir until mixture is thickened.
Cover and simmer 2 to 3 more minutes. Drain potatoes, carrots and onions.
Combine with cooked cabbage. Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: brown betty
directions: Put a layer of apples, then sugar, lemon and crumbs.
Add 1 cup of water before you put into the oven.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Cover the dish for the first 20 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg and parsley.
Shape into 24 meatballs.
In skillet, brown meatballs.
Pour off drippings. Stir in soup and water.
Cover.
Cook over low heat 20 minutes. Stir often.
Serve with rice, noodles or as a main dish with vegetables.

title: lasagne beef roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagne noodles in boiling water according to package directions.
Drain.
Rinse under cold water; drain.
Cook beef and onions in large skillet until beef is brown.
Drain.
Mix beef mixture with cheese, eggs, bread and seasonings.
Spread about 1/4 cup meat mixture over one noodle.
Roll up jelly roll fashion. Repeat for all noodles.
Mix tomato sauce and garlic.
Put half of sauce mixture over bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put roll-ups on top of sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over rolls. (Refrigerate, covered, if made ahead.)
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until warmed through.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil
potatoes	only until fork-tender.
Peel and grate roughly
on
large	side
of
hand	grater.
Place in buttered casserole.	Combine
other	ingredients in a saucepan and heat just
enough to melt cheese while stirring.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate 24 hours.	Bake uncovered one hour at 350°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer the ingredients in a 2-quart casserole, mixing the mayonnaise and Thousand Island dressing together first.
Bake in a 350° oven until heated through.
(I rinse the sauerkraut so it isn't quite as strong, optional.)

title: black magic dessert
directions: Melt chocolate chips, 3 tbsp. water, 1 tbsp. sugar in a pan. Gradually stir in 4 egg yolks (well beaten).
Beat gradually and let cool.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff.
Add to the mixture. Fold in one package of Dream Whip (whipped).
Cut cake into bite size pieces.
Grease 8 x 12 pan.
Layer cake pieces, then chocolate mixture.....end with chocolate.
Chill.

title: fricase' de pollo(chicken stew)
directions: Soak rice in large pot with water to cover.
Set aside.
Wash chicken pieces, pat dry with paper towels and place in large mixing bowl.
Put the garlic, peppercorns, oregano and paprika in a mortar and pound until crushed.
Rub this seasoning thoroughly into the chicken pieces, including liver, gizzard and neck.
Mix olive oil and vinegar.
Pour over chicken.
Cover bowl and set aside for chicken pieces to absorb flavors.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Stir bananas and lemon juice together.
Then mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into molds and freeze.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients until forms a ball. Divide dough into 48 balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden and puffy.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix well and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and while hot, frost with the following frosting.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed together and heat to dissolve the sugar.
Place cucumbers, onions and peppers in large container.
Pour heated mixture over them.
Refrigerate 5 days; stir once a day.
Freeze in jars or flat layers.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Use a glass bowl and wooden spoon.
Do not use metal. Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Stir in the rest of the water, flour and sugar.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon half and half and sugar until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup half and half into mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices, mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes 8 servings. Prep time:
15 minutes.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs with milk; add to dry ingredients.
Add currants.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick dough (add more milk if too dry).
Fry on electric grill at 325° (stove-top grill 400°); turn once.
For cutting out, a doughnut cutter without the center works well.
Do not burn!

title: lucky if you get a piece
directions: Combine mixture and press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: washboard cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in soda water and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Take dough size of a small egg, roll in hands, then make oblong and press down with fork.
(If too sticky to handle, add a little flour.)

title: easy lasagna
directions: Boil noodles in water with a little oil in it.
Set aside. Brown ground beef; do not drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese with the 3 eggs and a little pepper.

Place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish in layers as follows: 3 noodles, a little meat and sauce, 3 to 4 slices cheese, 3 noodles, eggs and cottage cheese, 3 noodles, rest of sliced cheese and rest of meat and sauce.
Sprinkle with lots of Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars, margarine and pecans over low heat; let cool. Mix sugar, buttermilk, soda, eggs, flour and vanilla; beat for 2 minutes.
Fold in candy mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake is done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all in a bowl and chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Set salad out 30 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: grandma's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix milk with cornstarch and set aside.
Beat eggs together and then add all other ingredients except milk mixture. After all other ingredients have been well blended, then add milk and cornstarch mixture.
Pour into uncooked pie shells.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake an additional 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: peanut butter dream bars
directions: Combine oats, flour, peanuts, sugar, soda and salt; mix well. Add margarine; mix until dry ingredients are thoroughly moistened and mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture; press remaining mixture onto bottom of greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Combine condensed milk and peanut butter in small bowl, mixing until well blended.
Spread over partially baked crust to within 1/4 inch from edge.
Combine reserved crumbs and M&M's; sprinkle over peanut butter mixture, pressing in lightly.
Continue baking for 20 to 22 minutes until golden brown. Cool before cutting.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Mix ingredients together, then mix artichoke juice, 3/4 teaspoon curry powder and 1/3 cup mayonnaise.
Add to rice mixture.
Serve warm or cold.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Boil sugar and water in large frying pan.
Shut off heat; add cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla (forms a syrup).
Stir in nuts until coated.
Spread nuts onto lightly buttered cookie sheet; let cool and dry.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain.
In pan, cook spaghetti and drain.
Rinse.
Combine sauce with beef and onions.
Combine soup and water.
Layer spaghetti, soup and meat in 2-quart greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Line casserole with a layer of chilies.
Cover with 1/2 the cheese.
Add rest of chilies and cover with rest of cheese.

title: hamburger french fry dinner
directions: Spread hamburger evenly over bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle seasoned salt and pepper over it.
Pour soup, mushrooms, water, milk, Gravy Master, Worcestershire sauce, onion soup mix and cheese over this.
Put potatoes over top evenly.
Pour 1 cup water over top and bake at 425° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: baked corn
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add all ingredients. Bake until golden brown, about 1 hour.

title: margaret's rice chili
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Season to taste.
In another boiler, add tomatoes, rice, chili powder and water.
Mix with ketchup.
Add meat and cook until rice is done.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients well; make into cakes.
Fry in oil until brown; turn to brown other side.
Serve hot.

title: meatball sauce
directions: Prepare meatballs, shaping approximately 2 pounds of ground beef into small balls.
Mix the ingredients together and heat well. Pour over meatballs; serve.

title: eve's pudding
directions: Peel and slice the apples and put them into a pie dish with 2 ounces of sugar, cinnamon and the water.
Cream the fat and remaining sugar and beat in the egg.
Stir in flour and baking powder. Spread this mixture on top of the fruit.
Bake in a moderately hot oven at 400° for about 1/2 hour until the fruit is cooked and the cake mixture well risen and golden.

title: hershey's soft and chewy cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
Add corn syrup, egg and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to butter mixture, beating well.
Stir in chips or bits.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned and almost set.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Cookies will be softer next day.

title: apple nut dessert
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, mix with a fork 1 cup sugar, 3/4 cup sifted flour, baking powder and soft shortening.
Stir in evaporated milk and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in broken nuts and apple until coated with batter.
Spread evenly in a greased 9-inch square pan.

title: spinach soup
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Pour off fat.
Add sausage to chopped spinach, water and bouillon cubes; heat thoroughly.
It is ready to serve.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger, saute vegetables and combine all in a crockpot.
Add water if it seems too thick.
Simmer as long as you like.

title: blueberry lemon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Combine flour, sugar, and lemon peel. Stir to mix. Remove 1/4 cup of the flour mixture and coat the blueberries with it. Beat together the eggs, lemon juice, vanilla extract, and whipping cream. Add the flour mixture and stir just until the dry ingredients are moistened. Do not overmix. Stir in blueberries. Spoon into a well greased muffin tin, filling each cup about 2/3 full. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into the center of a muffin. Remove muffins from pan immediately. Serve warm with butter. Makes 12 muffins.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Line a small loaf pan with foil paper.
Cover bottom of pan with vanilla wafers.
Mix together milk, lemon juice and whipped topping.
Pour over crackers and put in freezer.
Allow mixture to freeze.
Leave in freezer until ready to serve.
Turn out on a platter and slice.
Garnish as desired.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, and eggs together.
Add molasses. Add dry ingredients with water and vinegar.
Drop from spoon or store in refrigerator for several hours.
Then roll in balls and then flatten with floured tumbler.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil peeled potatoes until tender.
Beat sour cream and cheese together; add hot potatoes and beat until smooth.
Add butter, chives and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a well greased 2 quart casserole; dot with butter and sprinkle paprika on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
Wonderful do-ahead dish for company.
Can be cooked ahead and reheated or made and stored in refrigerator and cooked just before serving.

title: grilled corn cocoons
directions: Mix mayonnaise, juice and seasonings.
Place each ear of corn in piece of foil.
Brush mixture on all sides of corn, roll foil around corn, sealing the edges.
Place corn on medium hot coals or racks.
Grill 20 to 30 minutes or until tender, turn 1/4 turn every 5 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup--with no cream
directions: You pronounce the "pao" in this recipe name like "pow," and that's the kind of flavor punch you get in this specialty from Sichuan.
There's plenty of ginger, garlic and fiery red peppers to dazzle the most jaded taste buds.

title: cinnamon-apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and vanilla. Add sifted ingredients. Add apples and nuts.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and broken up or chopped broccoli in oil very slowly until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well (use a very large skillet as it makes a bountiful supply).
Place in greased casserole and bake in moderate oven (350°) 15 to 20 minutes.

title: gnocchi verdi con burro basilico(spinach and ricotta dumplings with basil)
directions: Drain Ricotta.
In large bowl, mix well Ricotta, spinach, eggs, salt, nutmeg and 1/2 cup Parmesan.
Gradually add only as much flour as mixture will absorb.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Bring large pot of water to boil.

title: thoroughbred pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, margarine and mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Add chocolate chips and pecans. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: poor man's lasagna
directions: Set 1/2 cup of Mozzarella cheese aside.
Put everything else in a casserole dish and top with the 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: glazed apple pie slices
directions: Make pie crust.
Divide into 2 balls.
Roll 1 ball on lightly floured surface to fit a 15 x 12-inch rectangle.
Fold in half, then in quarters.
Place on a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan and open out to fit.
Sprinkle Corn Flakes over dough.
In large bowl, toss apples with lemon juice.
Spread over dough.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and salt and sprinkle over apples.
Dot with butter. Roll remaining ball of dough out to 15 x 12-inch and fit on top of apples.
Prick crust with fork to allow steam to escape.
Seal edges.
Brush with egg.
Bake at 350° for about an hour until golden brown.

title: quick can-can stew
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan.
Add onion and cook until onion is soft, about 3 minutes.
Add salt, chili powder, soups, beans and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over corn chips.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs in 1-quart casserole.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in a pan of hot water.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and cut into pieces.
Mix all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Add a little water if dry.
Place in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves about 50.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and broth together.
Pour 1/3 in bottom of casserole.
Place chicken meat in bottom of casserole. Add peas, then cover with dry stuffing mix.
Pour rest of liquid on top of stuffing. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: garden summer salad
directions: Wash and slice cucumber.
Peel and slice onion in thin slices to form rings. Cut tomato in bite size chunks.
Place all in medium bowl. Add enough water to barely cover and add vinegar to taste. Salt and pepper to taste. Stir well and allow to sit a few minutes or longer.

title: chocolate peanut butter roll
directions: Melt chocolate chips over low heat.
Remove from heat and add water and honey.
Do not return to heat. Mix with spoon until chocolate mixture looses shine and forms ball in center of pan. Roll out between 2 pieces of wax paper to size 10 x 12.
Spread peanut butter over entire chocolate and roll out.
Remove top piece of wax paper.
Using bottom piece of wax paper (long end) roll up as for jelly roll.
Cool in refrigerator approximately 1 hour or until firm enough to cut.

title: christmas bean salad(a sweet and sour salad)
directions: Mix green beans, peas, celery, bell pepper, onion, and pimento together in medium bowl.

title: crunchy nut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets and bake until brown at 350°.
Yields about 40 cookies.

title: vena's italian torte
directions: Slice toast lengthwise.
Place layer of toast in 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Cook vanilla pudding; stir for 2 or 3 minutes after cooking.
Pour mixture over toast.
Add another layer of toast slices.

title: green bean pie
directions: Pan-fry the ground beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Add the green beans and tomato soup.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put in square baking dish.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Spread potatoes over meat and beans.
Garnish with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or in microwave until bubbly.

title: rice meat balls
directions: Combine rice from directions on box and mix all together. Shape into 18 balls, using only 1/2 cup juice. Put in skillet and pour remaining juice over meat balls.

title: herbed "n" spiced chicken(eating light)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix together yogurt and curry powder.
Pour dry stuffing mix into blender and process until crumbs form.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; brush with yogurt mix and roll in stuffing crumbs.

title: antipasto
directions: Partially cook asparagus in boiling water 1 to 2 minutes; drain.
Chill in ice water; drain.
(If using frozen asparagus, thaw and drain.)
Partially cook cauliflower 2 to 3 minutes in boiling water; drain.
Chill in ice water; drain.
Place asparagus, cauliflower, cucumber, carrots, and mushrooms in 13 x 9-inch baking dish, keeping vegetables separated from one another. Pour dressing over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Spoon dressing over vegetables occasionally.
Drain vegetables well.
Line large platter or serving tray with leaf lettuce.
Arrange marinated vegetables, artichoke hearts, olives, pepperoncini, beets, tomatoes, cheese, and salami on platter. Serves 6 as a main dish.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Heat shortening slowly in deep kettle to 350°.
Peel and slice onions 1/4-inch thick.
Separate rings.
Dip into milk, then into flour and salt, which have been sifted together.
Fry a few onions rings at a time in hot shortening, until golden brown, 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain well over kettle, then place on tray covered with absorbent paper.
Serve hot.

title: oven stew
directions: Use 2 1/2-quart or larger casserole dish.
Place uncooked meat in bottom.
Season to taste, then layer the vegetables as listed except potatoes.
Pour tomato sauce and water.
Cover and bake 3 hours at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Add potatoes.
Cover and bake 45 minutes more.

title: vegetable curry dip(serves 50)
directions: Mix all ingredients together very well and place in sealed container in refrigerator for 24 hours before using.
Dip will last in refrigerator for 6 months.
Good for all cold or hot vegetables.

title: pineapple glaze
directions: In covered blender, blend all ingredients until smooth on low. Makes 1 cup.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Gradually add to softened cream cheese.
Blend well. Chill until almost firm.
Fold in nuts, marshmallows and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch pan or skillet. Combine all ingredients and bake 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: kluski casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Add onion to drippings and saute 5 minutes.
Then add cabbage, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package.
Drain.
Stir in cottage cheese, Muenster and dill.
Add bacon and cabbage mixture. Put in greased 3-quart dish.
Sprinkle on cracker crumbs.
Drizzle with butter.
Add paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: In a saucepan, bring first four ingredients to a boil and cook for 8 minutes.
Add vanilla and store in refrigerator.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Combine apples and cider in 3-quart slow cooking pot.
Cover and cook 8 hours, or until apples are soft.
Puree in food processor or food mill.
Return to pot and add sugar and spices. Cover and cook on low for 1 to 2 hours longer.
If thicker consistency is desired, uncover and cook longer.

title: skillet macaroni
directions: In large skillet, brown hamburger, onion and green pepper. When meat loses its red color, stir in tomatoes, macaroni, sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or when macaroni is done.

title: oysters rockefeller(for 4 dozen oysters)
directions: Grind spinach, onions, celery and parsley very fine.
Mix in 1 pound butter (melted) and 1 1/2 cups bread crumbs.
Season with Worcestershire sauce, anchovy paste, salt and hot sauce to taste. Put oysters in shells, which are on rock salt, and cover each with some sauce.
Cover with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake in 450° oven until brown.
Serve hot.
Serves 4. Sauce may be frozen, but do not add wine until sauce is thawed and ready to spread on oysters.

title: white mountain frosting or icing
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until it spins a 6 to 8-inch thread.
Beat egg whites until they stand in stiff peaks.
Pour hot syrup slowly into beaten egg whites and beat until stiff peaks form.
Add vanilla and blend.
Frost cake.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel and remove avocados.
Mash avocados.
Mix in tomatoes, onion and lemon juice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with tortilla chips and salsa.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, water chestnuts, pimentos, almonds, mushrooms, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Place in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bachelor's icing
directions: Cream shortening with salt and flavoring until smooth and fluffy.
Slowly add sugar (as you heat).
Add 4 teaspoons milk after each box of sugar.
Leftover icing can be frozen to use later.

title: doughnut balls
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add milk, oil and egg; beat well.
Use enough cooking oil to half fill a deep saucepan. (You can also use a deep fryer.)
Drop from a teaspoon into hot oil; fry until done (2 to 3 minutes).
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: company beets
directions: Mix and cook until thick last 5 ingredients.
Place beets and pineapple in casserole.
Pour sauce over.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain. Put in crock-pot in layers with cheese, saving 1/2 cup cheese for top. (Also salt, pepper and margarine for layers.) Beat eggs well; add evaporated and sweet milk. Pour mixture over macaroni; put rest of cheese on top. Cook for 3 hours on low.

title: catfish stew
directions: Fry bacon; crumble.
Saute onion in bacon grease and drain well.
Boil catfish 10 to 15 minutes or until meat falls off the bone.
Remove bones and skin.
Add potatoes, tomatoes, onion and bacon in with meat.
Season to taste with Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper.
The more Tabasco sauce the better!
Let simmer 30 minutes.

title: ham stack-ups
directions: Stack tortillas; cut tortillas into 6-inch squares. Set aside. Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add cream cheese and next 7 ingredients. Process until mixture is smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides. Layer tortillas, spreading each evenly with about 3 tablespoons cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle top with pecans. Cover and chill 8 hours.

title: apple rolls
directions: Make pie crust.
Roll and cover with chopped apples. Roll and cut in slices.
Place in a 9 x 14-inch pan. Simmer water, sugar and margarine.
Pour over apple slices.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt butter or oleo over low heat.
Add marshmallows and heat until completely melted.
Remove from heat and stir in Rice Krispies until completely coated.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Heat undiluted soup; add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Mash cream cheese; add to soup and continue cooking until dissolved.
Cool, then fold in mayonnaise.
Add chopped shrimp, vegetables and seasonings.
Mix well and pour into oiled fish mold or any type of mold.
Serves 8.

title: cut-out sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter flavor Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended. Beat in egg.

title: pie dough for fried pies
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cut shortening into flour mixture to resemble coarse meal.
Beat 1 egg.
Add 6 1/2 ounces Carnation milk.
Mix and divide into 2 rolls.
Freeze and use as needed. Note:
I pull off a piece of dough, a little larger that a golf ball, roll out and place a saucer on it.
Cut around the saucer. You have a perfect round circle.
I use any can fruit pie filling. Place 1 teaspoon fruit in center of pie dough.
Fold over and be sure you have it pinched together good (or the juice from the fruit will run out).
Best fried in electric skillet.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
Stir together cereal and milk.
Let stand 2 minutes. Add egg and Crisco.
Beat well. Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined. Fill 12 greased muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes or until brown.

title: herbal hot tea
directions: Cautions:
Not all herbs are suitable for making tea.
Know about the herb you are using.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in cream in top of a double boiler.
Mix dates, cherries and pecans; add to marshmallow mixture.
Add 1/2 of crumbs, salt and vanilla to fruit mixture.
Mix well to form "dough".
Put rest of crumbs on waxed paper and roll dough in crumbs, shaping it into a loaf or roll.
Wrap in waxed paper, Saran Wrap or foil and store in refrigerator.

title: susan's famous punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water well.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Mix and pour into clean milk jugs.
(You will need 2 for each making of punch.)
Place in freezer (do not fill jug completely to allow for expansion).
Take frozen mixture out of freezer approximately 1 hour before use.
Cut jug away and place in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over frozen mixture.
Chop frozen mixture to make a slushy texture.
Serves approximately 50.

title: never fail fruit pie
directions: In a Pyrex dish, stir fruit, 1 cup sugar and water real good. Then make a batter of flour, 1/2 cup sugar and melted margarine. Mix and pour over fruit or put in the bottom of baking dish and put fruit on top.
It turns out the same way.
I put my crust (batter) on top and Bertha puts hers on the bottom.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: crescent chick-be-quicks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
In small bowl, combine French fried onions, flour and salt.
Blend well. Set aside.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Cut each in half to make 16 triangles.
Dip chicken pieces in beaten egg; coat with onion mixture.
Place one coated piece on wide end of each triangle; roll to opposite point.
Place point side down on greased cookie sheet.
Brush tops with remaining egg; sprinkle with seeds.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 16 snacks.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrots in butter for 10 minutes.
Add flour to sauteed mixture, stirring well.
Cook 1 minute.
Combine broth and half and half.
Stir into vegetable mixture, cook over medium heat, stir constantly until thick.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Add chicken and stir well.
Pour chicken mixture into a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Top with pastry.
I use 2 ready-made pie crusts.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown the beef and onion; drain grease.
Mash potatoes with milk and butter.
In a casserole dish, layer with beef and onion, then the corn.
Cover with mashed potatoes; sprinkle with cheese.

title: west of the pecos casserole
directions: Brown meat in butter with green
pepper, onion
and Worcestershire sauce.
Add corn, soup and tomatoes.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook noodles; drain and add to rest of ingredients in baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: martha's bran bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased bread pan.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except peppers.
Cook peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Stuff loosely with mixture.
Stand upright in baking dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce and water over peppers.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: the best ever irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and generously grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf tin.
Mix, but do not cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, caraway seed, raisins and sour cream.
Stir after each addition.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda together in separate bowl and add to other mixture.
Mix, batter will be stiff.
Spoon into greased loaf pan and bake 15 minutes at 400° and lower oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and immediately turn out on a wire rack to cool.
Place loaf on side while cooling.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together thoroughly and refrigerate.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Boil the water. Add the cornstarch and stir and boil until clear. Pour this over the sugar and butter. When cold, add lemon and egg yolks. Pour into plate lined with crust. Bake in hot oven, having the greatest heat at bottom of oven. When nearly done, cover with meringue made of the beaten egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar. Return to the oven and brown.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Cook onions and tomatoes until onions are soft.
Reduce to low heat.
Cut up cheese; stir in gradually until all cheese is melted.
Add chiles to mixture.
Simmer very low.
Put in crock-pot to keep warm.
Serve with nacho flavored Doritos.

title: salt substitute
directions: Combine all ingredients in a salt shaker and serve in place of salt.
Use coarsely ground spices for a better texture.
Makes 1/3 of a cup. Recipe may be doubled.

title: sugar pecans
directions: Cook all ingredients except pecans until it forms a soft ball in water.
Add pecans and stir.
Pour on waxed paper and cool.

title: barley pilaf
directions: Cook chopped onions in margarine until wilted.
Remove onions and add barley to margarine.
Cook slowly until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Mix onion, browned barley, mushroom and chicken broth in casserole.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Bake covered for 2 hours at 350° until barley is tender.

title: cheesy chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat large nonstick skillet sprayed with cooking oil on medium heat.
Add chicken; cook and stirring about 6 minutes or until cooked through.
Add 1/2 cup of the salsa and 2/3 cup of cheese; mix lightly.
Spread 1 cup of remaining salsa onto bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon 1/4 cup of chicken mixture down the center of each tortilla shell and roll up.
Place tortilla seam down in prepared dish.
Top with remaining salsa and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with corn.

title: chicken pie
directions: Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle chicken, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 400° until golden brown (35 to 40 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Refrigerate unused pie.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add
eggs,
one
at a time. Add vanilla wafer crumbs alternately with milk.
Fold in nuts, coconut and vanilla extract.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and black bean enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Coat shallow baking pan with cooking spray and set aside. In a large bowl, combine beans, chili powder, cumin, jalapeno and 1/2 cup of salsa.
