Mash with fork until blended. Spoon mixture onto center of each tortilla. Place chicken over bean mixture. Roll up tortillas, fold in ends and place side by side in bottom of prepared pan. Top with salsa, cheese and scallions. Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 more minutes, until cheese is golden.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into 9-inch deep pie crust. Bake at 425° approximately 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: witches brew
directions: Boil the cider, sugar, butter and cinnamon together until foamy.
Remove from heat and pour in the Southern Comfort.
Can be served from a hollowed out pumpkin.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles in boiling salt water about 12 minutes. Rinse and drain.
Saute beef and onion in large skillet or microwave; drain fat.
Add all remaining ingredients except cheese. Simmer for 25 minutes or micro-simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: chow mein cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add noodles and marshmallows; stir well. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and let set until cool.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: In medium bowl, combine crumbs, 2 Tbsp. parmesan cheese, oregano, garlic powder, and pepper.
Rinse chicken and roll in crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken in a 2 quart flat baking dish.
In another bowl, blend soup, milk, and 2 Tbsp. parmesan cheese.
Add another dash of garlic powder and sprinkle of oregano.
Stir with a fork.
Pour over chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkles with remains of crumb mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake 40 minutes at 350 degrees.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: frosty fill-ups(excellent summer club refreshments)
directions: In a large glass, place a scoop of each of the flavors of sherbet.
Combine all the other ingredients and pour enough of this juice over the sherbet to fill the glasses.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° until crust is done.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Blend baking mix, 1/2 cup granulated sugar and 3 tablespoons cocoa in 8-inch square baking dish (greased).
Stir in milk and vanilla until well blended.
Sprinkle evenly with rest of cocoa and granulated sugar.
Pour on water.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until top is firm.
Dust with confectioners sugar. Serve at once with sauce over cake.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: fish batter
directions: Dip fish into batter and roll in cracker crumbs.
Deep fry.

title: tomato soup cream cheese frosting cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, sift ingredients.
Add shortening and 1/2 can of soup. Beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts, raisins, remaining soup and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn onto rack and cool completely.
Frost.

title: jonathan's homemade pizza
directions: This is a great recipe to prepare with your children.

title: white punch
directions: Mix Sprite and juice.
Add sherbet and ice cream just before serving.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Line large pizza pan with cookie dough, pressing to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cookie crust.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese.
Glaze with a mixture of marmalade and water.
Chill.
Makes 12 or more servings.

title: 6-week raisin bran muffins
directions: In a huge bowl, mix well first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Store in a tightly covered container in the refrigerator.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
(Batter keeps for up to 6 weeks.
Simply scoop out desired quantity, then return unused batter to the refrigerator.)

title: chicken or turkey hot dish
directions: Blend soup, 3/4 cup milk, meat, vegetables and half the cheese and onions.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the Bisquick, 1/4 cup milk and egg.
Spoon over the chicken mixture.
(Will be about 8 spoonfuls over top of pan.)
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining cheese and onions over top.
Return to oven and bake an additional 3 to 5 minutes. Serves 8.

title: brown rice stir-fry
directions: Heat a deep, 12-inch frypan on medium-high heat.
Add oils. Add garlic; stir until toasted.
Add onions; stir quickly.
Before onions start to brown, add cabbage and chicken broth.
Stir and cook for 3 minutes.
Add zucchini and snow peas and a splash or two of soy sauce.
Stir and cook for 5 minutes.
Add cilantro, meats, rice, garlic powder and carrot.
Simmer for 2 minutes. Serve with soy sauce.

title: berried delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.

title: fluffy pumpkin casserole
directions: Combine pumpkin, eggs, orange juice, sugar and milk. Beat well. Add salt and margarine. Mix well. Add baking powder. Pour into deep greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm all the way to the center. Serve as a vegetable with chicken, turkey or pork.

title: marinade for chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a shallow baking dish.
Place chicken in marinade overnight.
Grill chicken, basting with marinade until done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown pork sausage.
Brown shoestring potatoes in skillet. Layer sausage, shoestring potatoes, scrambled eggs and cheese in long casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then serve.

title: cheese crock
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Beat in Cheddar cheese until blended. Add Blue cheese. Gradually add enough brandy to make a creamy spread. Add red pepper and stir in nuts. Pack in a crock or mold. Cover tightly with plastic wrap or foil. Chill until serving time.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, pepper and cucumber.
Blend in mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Chill.
Before serving, add 2 chopped tomatoes.

title: herbed round steak
directions: Cut meat in pieces.
Sprinkle with salts and pepper.
Roll in flour and brown both sides in hot oil.
Drain and place in crock-pot.
Cook onion in reserved drippings.
Spoon over meat. Mix celery soup and spices.
Spoon mixture over steak and cook until tender.
When tender, mix flour with cold water and add to mixture to thicken gravy.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.

title: pumpkin squares with cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and pumpkin until fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet (15 x 10 x 1-inch). Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and pour in a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms well and plunge into a large kettle of boiling salted water.
Cover and cook for 12 to 15 minutes.
In separate pot, combine cider vinegar, 1 cup water, salt, sugar and all the spices.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. With slotted spoon, transfer mushrooms to jars.
Pour room temperature marinade over mushrooms to cover.
Seal and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together; roll in shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: microwave blueberry crunch
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients until crumbly. Press half of the crumbs into an 8-inch square dish. Reserve other half. Microwave sugar, cornstarch and water on High for 2 to 4 minutes, stirring several times until thick and clear. Stir in blueberries, vanilla and lemon flavoring until well mixed. Pour the mixture over crumbs in dish. Sprinkle reserved crumbs over the top and microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes. Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Prepare stuffing using 1 cup water, 1/2 cup margarine and bouillon.
Saute onions and celery in 1/2 cup butter.
Brown sausage and add with drippings, pecans and eggs.
Mix well.
Brown lightly before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese filling alternately with dry ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into a greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or done.
Serve with Apricot Butter.

title: gloop(for kids 3 years old or older)
directions: Pour the white glue into a clean, empty peanut butter jar.
Add 1/2 cup water and 10 drops of food coloring; stir.
Combine the borax and a cup of water in a medium size plastic bowl.
Slowly pour the glue mixture into the borax solution; stir until well mixed.
The borax caused the mixture to congeal.
Scoop the gloop out of the water and knead in your hands until dry enough to play with.
Store in a sealed container or plastic bag and will keep for several weeks.
Gloop dries out after a lot of handling.
Gloop can be pulled to and fro for a snap and crackly tug of war.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
In a separate skillet, saute meat, onions and peppers in Worcestershire sauce.
May need to add a small amount of water until meat is done.
Stir occasionally.
Cook on medium to start and then on low until done. Pour over rice.
Top with picante sauce and shredded cheese. Serves 6.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion until golden; add meat and seasoning.
Brown.
Add drained beans and soup; pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mash the potatoes; add the milk, egg and seasonings.
Spoon in mounds over meat.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 13-inch pan. Stir brownie mix, eggs, oil and water until well blended (about 50 strokes).
Set aside.

title: sour cream enchilada casserole
directions: Combine water and 2 tablespoons picante sauce in large, shallow dish.
Place tortillas in mixture and let stand 5 minutes. Drain.
Brown beef and drain fat or cook and debone chicken, if using chicken.
Stir in salt, pepper, cumin, chili powder, olives and 1/4 cup picante sauce.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat 1/2-inch strips about 1 1/2 inches long.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add mushrooms and onion; cook and stir until onion is tender then remove from skillet.
In same skillet cook meat until brown.
Stir in broth (reserving 1/3 cup) catsup and garlic. Cover; simmer 15 minutes.

title: fish sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together well in a saucepan.
Bring to boil and then simmer for 20 minutes.
Very good hot or cold.

title: gateau a la bouielle
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions. Pour batter into greased 14 x 11 1/2 pan (do not bake now). Bring milk and water to a boil.

title: all day stew
directions: Put in pan and bake at 250° for 6 hours.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Add chopped bananas, chopped pecans and Cool Whip. Freeze.

title: special k chewies
directions: Melt corn syrup and sugar on low heat.
When melted, take off burner and stir in peanut butter, then crunch cereal up and stir into mixture.
Then spread on cookie sheet.
Let cool, then cut in squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onions together.
Drain and add the margarine.
Melt cheese and blend with soup.
Mix together and pour into buttered casserole.
Prepare stuffing as directed on package and spread over top.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cream-filled strawberries
directions: Begin about 30 minutes before serving or early in day.
Cut stem ends of strawberries.
With sharp knife, cut deep "X" in top of each fruit.
With fingertips, gently spread each strawberry apart to make "petals"; set aside.
In small bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat heavy or whipping cream until stiff peaks form. In large bowl, with wire whisk, prepare instant pudding as label directs but use only 1 cup milk.
With wire whisk or rubber spatula, gently fold whipped cream and almond extract into prepared instant pudding.

title: mixed vegetables
directions: In large skillet, melt butter or margarine and lightly saute green pepper and onions.
Add zucchini, corn and seasonings.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook 1 to 2 minutes more.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Whip milk and pudding until stiff.
Add vanilla to flavor (about 1 teaspoon).
Add whipped cream to pudding mixture.
Mix 10 minutes more at medium speed.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Makes 1 large pie.
Broil coconut and sprinkle on top.

title: 5 minute chocolate mousse
directions: Combine pudding and milk.
Stir 1 minute.
Stir in Cool Whip. Refrigerate.
Garnish with Cool Whip and chocolate curls.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll crescent dough, leaving it in one piece and place on 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet, stretching and spreading to cover entire bottom of cookie sheet, pinching together any holes.
Bake until golden brown according to crescent instruction.
Cool and set aside.
Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese, sour cream and Ranch dressing until smooth and creamy.
Spread on cooled crescent crust. Sprinkle cauliflower, broccoli, carrots and mushrooms on top of spread.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients; put into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
During the last 10 minutes, uncover and brown lightly.

title: quick cookies
directions: Beat all
together
by hand.
(Add whatever you want to batter.)
Drop
by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: tex-mex sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, melt 1 cup margarine; stir in 1/4 cup cocoa and 1 tablespoon coffee, then water.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
In large mixer bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add cocoa mixture; mix well.
Stir in 1/3 cup sweetened condensed milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
In small saucepan, melt remaining 1/4 cup margarine; stir in remaining 1/4 cup cocoa and 1 tablespoon coffee.
Add remaining sweetened condensed milk; stir in confectioners sugar and nuts.
Spread on warm cake.

title: moussaka
directions: Saute meat, onion and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain well. Add tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes. Brush eggplant with olive oil and broil for 5 minutes on each side.
Make layers of eggplant and meat sauce in greased casserole.
Top with cottage cheese and eggs beaten together. Sprinkle with little nutmeg.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 hours. Serves 4.

title: cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in order listed.
Can use mixer up to oats, then have to hand mix.
Use ice cream scoop.
Four cookies to an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
I use red and green M&M's at Christmas and make cookies smaller. Also roll and freeze to make sliced cookies.

title: on the double dinner rolls(low-fat)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Add sugar, salt, Butter Buds and one cup of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in the rest of the flour and continue stirring until smooth.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until it doubles in size (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Spoon batter into 24 muffin cups sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Fill each cup about 1/2 full.
Let rise until dough reaches the top of muffin tins (20 to 30 minutes).
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 24 rolls.
Fat:
0.21 g. Cal:
96. Cholesterol:
0 mg.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until tender; debone and cut into cubes.
Cook pepper, onion and celery in small bit of water.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth until almost done.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer awhile, until spaghetti is done.
Top with cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: spaghetti alla carbonara (with bacon)
directions: Start the spaghetti cooking in boiling water while browning bacon in oil.
Drain bacon and set aside.
In bowl, mix eggs, salt, pepper, cream and Parmesan cheese.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together, then make small balls.
Melt slowly the semi-sweet chocolate chips with wax.
Dip with toothpicks onto wax paper and let cool.
Makes a bunch.

title: avocado dip for taco salad
directions: Cream avocado dip, cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread in center of large plate.
Top with rest of ingredients.
Surround with nacho chips.

title: strawberry ice cream soda
directions: In a tall glass, stir together 1/4 cup club soda and syrup. Add ice cream.
Fill glass with additional club soda.
Stir gently.
Serve immediately.
Makes 1 serving.

title: picante sauce
directions: Cover with water and boil until tomato skins start to split (about 10 minutes). 1 large onion - minced in food processor. Process tomatoes and peppers (use some of water if necessary).
Mix all ingredients.
Add 2 tablespoons minced garlic.
Salt to taste. Seal while hot.
Makes 7 pints.

title: bagels
directions: Knead together ingredients until soft.
Let rise until twice its size.
Cut into 12 portions.
Roll into soft ball.
Make a hole in center with thumb (should resemble a doughnut).
Place on a greased cookie sheet with wax paper lining.
Cover with a wet towel and place in a warm place for 30 to 40 minutes, until double in size.
Dip each ring into boiling water for 2 minutes, turning twice.
Place on a lightly oiled baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In glass bowl, combine the onions, 2 tablespoons chillies and 1 tablespoon butter.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Add taco sauce, 1/4 cup sour cream and chili powder.
Stir in turkey and 1/2 cup cheese.
Divide the mixture among tortillas.
Place seam side down in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Microwave remaining 2 tablespoons butter until melted.
Blend in flour. Slowly stir in broth.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes until thickened, stirring every minute.
Stir in the remaining sour cream and chillies.
Pour over enchiladas.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and tomato.
Microwave until cheese is melted.

title: crispy crumb fried chicken
directions: Combine stuffing mix, salt, pepper and paprika on wax paper. Moisten chicken with water.
Coat with crumbs.
Heat shortening in electric skillet on medium heat or in a heavy skillet.
Fry chicken, turn once for even browning.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook chicken for 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain on paper towels.

title: unbelievable macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Combine all ingredients in deep baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. When done, you may want to sprinkle top with cheese and run under broiler.

title: favorite potatoes
directions: Let potatoes thaw slightly and break apart.
Spread in 2 1/2-quart ungreased casserole.
In a mixing bowl, combine onion, garlic salt, soup and sour cream. Spread this on top of potatoes and mix. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Remove from oven and top with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted. Serves 6.

title: korean dish
directions: Trim off fat and cut pork chops into small squares.
Put carrots, onion, celery and pork chops in big iron skillet with water and soy sauce to taste and 2 or 3 tablespoons of sugar sprinkled over all.
Cover; cook slowly for about 45 minutes, or done to your taste.
Make 2 or 3 cups of Minute rice; serve with vegetables on top.
Serves 6.

title: greek stew
directions: Heat oil in skillet. When hot, add onion and cook 5 minutes. Add beans and pepper and saute until onion is translucent, about 3 minutes. Add zucchini, potatoes and parsley. Pour tomatoes and juice over vegetables. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 45 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Can serve hot or at room temperature.

title: ruby pickle's dressing
directions: Chop finely the onion and celery.
Mix together and cook until tender in a small amount of broth.
Warm the remaining broth. Finely crumble the cornbread, biscuits and bread, stir in the sage and pepper, add onion mixture and approximately 3 quarts warm broth.
Mix well.
(This should be juicy.)
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir well and add more broth if needed. Bake uncovered 20 minutes or more until browned to taste.

title: cheesy drop biscuits
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients until well blended. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan. Yields 2 dozen.

title: chewy, chocolatey cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well. Combine dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts, if desired.

title: baked bean and sausage casserole
directions: Follow directions on lima bean package, except cook only 10 minutes.
Drain and gently mix with baked beans and kidney beans; set aside.
Place sausage in skillet with a little water.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Pan-fry until brown; don't prick.
Cut sausage into 2 or 3 pieces.
Heat oven to 400°.
Cut ham into 1/2-inch cubes.
Add sausage and ham to beans.
Combine all other ingredients together; add to beans.
Pour bean mixture into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake uncovered 1 hour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure; add baking powder and salt and sift again.
Cream butter thoroughly; add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla; add flour and blend.
Chill 10 to 15 minutes.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake 10 to 12 minutes in hot oven.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: spiced pecan halves
directions: Boil sugar, cinnamon and evaporated milk to soft ball stage. Add pecan halves and vanilla.
Put onto wax paper and let dry.

title: my favorite corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp. Remove.
Pour off drippings. Return 3 tablespoons to pan.
Add onion.
Cook until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer a few minutes.
Crumble bacon on top. Delicious!

title: hot fudge brownies
directions: Make brownie mix and let cool.
After cool, cut into 2-inch squares.
Add a scoop of ice cream on top.
Add Hot Fudge Sauce, whipped cream and nuts.
Mum, mum, good!

title: foo man chew
directions: Place oil in skillet, add onion, saute for five minutes, add ground beef.
When meat is brown, combine with all other ingredients, pour into a large baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with chow mein noodles, bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes longer.

title: holiday fruit jello
directions: Make
package lime Jell-O
according
to
directions. When Jell-O begins to
shake
(partially set) spoon some into a serving (fancy glass) bowl, put
in a layer of the fruits, then add more Jell-O and more fruit until you have finished the lime Jell-O. Then do the
same thing with the raspberry (or cherry) Jell-O, waiting until the lime Jell-O is pretty much set before adding the raspberry Jell-O on
top of the lime Jell-O and then add the fruit.
Set until firm before serving.

title: stew beef casserole
directions: Place in casserole
dish or bean pot.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: colorful pasta salad(also suitable for diabetic food plans.)
directions: In a large bowl, combine oil, vinegar, pepper, garlic, salt, oregano, onion and sweetener.
Cook macaroni according to package instructions. Add cooked macaroni, beans and mixed vegetables. Toss well. Cover and chill.
Take out of refrigerator and toss 2 or more times and again before serving.
Makes 16 servings.

title: aunt helen's hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients and onion.
Add buttermilk and eggs. Stir just enough to moisten cornmeal.
Drop rounded teaspoons in deep fat at 375°.
Fry until golden brown, turning once (about 2 minutes each side).
Drain and serve at once.
Yield:
About 80 puppies.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Gently add blueberries. Pour into a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle topping.

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Add all ingredients together, except coconut.
Mix well. Chill in refrigerator.
Form into balls.
Roll in coconut.
Makes 60 to 70.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
Allow to rest for 2 minutes.
Pour into a large mixing bowl.
Add milk, softened margarine, the sugar replacement or fructose, egg, salt and 1 1/2 cups of the flour.
Beat on low to blend, then on high for 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining 1 cup of flour.
Transfer to a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl, turn dough over and cover with plastic wrap and then a towel.
Allow to rise until double in size.
Punch dough down and roll into a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
If using Stevia Rebaudiana, dissolve it in the melted margarine, spread dough surface with the melted margarine mixture and sprinkle with desired amount of cinnamon.

title: chicken fried steak with cream gravy
directions: Cover bottom of heavy skillet with cooking oil or melted shortening; start heating at medium-high temperature.
Beat egg and 1/4 cup milk together in shallow bowl.

Toss meat, 1 or 2 pieces at a time, in 1 cup flour in a gallon size plastic bag. Dip flour covered meat 1 at a time in egg/milk, then toss again in flour (may need to add more flour); place in medium-hot oil in skillet (cram them all in there; they will shrink a lot).
Turn when very light brown/golden on bottom.
Reduce heat slightly and place lid on pan for 10 minutes, checking occasionally to make sure they don't burn.
Remove lid and increase heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Done in 1 minute or so, when crispy again. Drain on paper towel.

title: icebox cake
directions: In a rectangular Pyrex baking dish, place graham crackers in pan to serve as bottom crust.
Use whole crackers.
Prepare vanilla pudding according to package directions (you can use low-fat milk if desired).
Pour over graham crackers.
Place another layer of graham crackers over pudding.
Prepare chocolate pudding according to package directions and pour over graham crackers.
Let cool in refrigerator until set and just before serving, arrange banana slices and cracker crumbs on top.
Cut into squares and lift out with a spatula.

title: bonbons
directions: We use about 2 quarts of pecans, chopped fine in the blender.

title: oven easy chicken
directions: Start heating oven to 425°.
Salt and pepper chicken to taste. Season flour with a little salt and pepper or seasoning of your choice.
Coat chicken with flour.
In shallow, open pan in oven, melt butter.
Remove pan from oven; in it, arrange chicken in single layer skin side down.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Turn; bake 15 minutes or
until brown and fork-tender.

title: beef with oyster sauce
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic and crushed red pepper in medium bowl.
Cut beef across grain into 1/4-inch slices; cut each slice into 2-inch pieces.
Toss beef with soy sauce mixture.
Marinate at room temperature 20 minutes or cover and refrigerate up to 8 hours.
Blend broth and oyster sauce into cornstarch in cup until smooth.
Heat large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add oil; heat until hot.
Add 1/2 of beef mixture; stir-fry until beef is barely pink in center.
Remove and reserve.
Repeat with remaining beef mixture; remove and reserve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter together in a bowl in the microwave. Add sugar; mix well with your hand. It will look like pie dough. Spread in a greased 9x13 pan. Melt chocolate bar and spread over fudge. Let cool; cut into squares.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except chicken.
It should be boiled until tender.
Take off bones and place in bottom of Pyrex dish or can be mixed with rest.
Save some crackers and cheese for top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix
marshmallows and
pineapple;
let	set
the
night before or the morning
of	serving
in refrigerator.
Beat 1/2 pint cream; add vanilla before serving.	Put all together with pineapple mixture and add walnuts and cherries.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in butter.
Add soups, sauce, milk and chile peppers to taste.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cut tortillas into quarters.
Spoon into casserole a layer of meat mixture followed with a layer of tortillas, and then a layer of grated cheese.
Continue until all meat mixture is used.
Bake in a medium oven for one hour.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients and pour over crackers.
Stir until well coated.

title: burritos
directions: Brown meat with onion and bell pepper.
Add taco seasoning as per directions.
Mix in beans over low heat.
When hot, spoon mixture onto tortilla.
Add halved Velveeta slices and roll up tortilla.
Heat on lightly oiled griddle or skillet until cheese begins to melt.

title: yellow squash muffins
directions: Cut
squash
in
1-inch
slices.
Cook in boiling water until tender.
Drain
well
and mash.
Measure 2 cups squash. Combine squash,
eggs
and	butter.
Stir well and set aside. Combine other ingredients.	Add to squash mixture.	Stir until just moistened.	Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Boil egg noodles.
When soft, drain.
Place in casserole dish. Add tuna after draining water off, then add cream of chicken soup.
Stir together well.
Salt and pepper to taste. Place in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.
It's then ready to eat.

title: mustard honey chicken breast
directions: Mix together mustard and honey.
Dip chicken pieces in mustard and honey and dip in bread crumbs.
Arrange pieces of chicken on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Turn pieces of chicken once.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until chilled.
Roll in small balls and press with fork or cut in strips or use cookie press.
Bake at 300° until slightly brown, about 15 minutes.
Yields 100.
Freezes well.

title: millionaires
directions: Unwrap caramels and melt with 2 tablespoons water in top of double boiler.
Add 2 cups chopped pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful onto buttered cookie sheets.
Refrigerate to cool.
Melt Hershey bars with paraffin in top of double boiler.
Use just enough paraffin so that chocolate will adhere to candies, gradually adding paraffin until right consistency.
Dip caramel/pecan candies into chocolate, using tongs.
Allow excess chocolate to drip back into pot.
Place on wax paper and allow to cool thoroughly in refrigerator.

title: chicken kabobs
directions: It's fast and easy.
Just put on a kabob stick, in any order, and barbecue for 15 minutes at medium heat.
That's it!
For the working mom, it's great!
Vanessa loves to make them!

title: quesadillas casserole
directions: In a small bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
Place 1 tortilla in an 8-inch round cake pan, sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Spread 1/4 of bean mixture over tortilla.
Repeat with second tortilla and bean mixture.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese over bean mixture. Repeat with remaining tortillas and bean mixture. Sprinkle remaining 1 cup cheese over top.

title: puppy chow
directions: Put the chocolate chips in the microwave for about 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir cereal into chips.
Pour mixture into bag with powdered sugar.
Shake well.
Makes 4 cups.

title: pickling peach pickles
directions: Peel peaches and place in large container.
Let stand 12 hours.
Pour juice into a container and let come to slow boil. Place peaches in juice and cook until tender.
Place in hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: curried sweet potato soup
directions: Bring 1/4 cup broth to a boil over medium-high heat.
Add onions and garlic and cook until liquid has almost evaporated. Add curry powder and paprika and stir to combine.
Add remaining broth and rest of ingredients except parsley.
Bring to boil and reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until sweet potatoes begin to fall apart.
Mash any remaining chunks with spoon. Stir in parsley.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings, 160 cal.; 0 cholesterol; 230 mg.
sodium; 490 mg. potassium.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spry 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in melted margarine; coat with remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a pan or pie plate. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a 2-quart glass bowl. Microwave at Medium (50% power) 4 to 5 minutes, stirring at 1 1/2 minute intervals.
Stir in walnuts and pour into a buttered 8-inch square dish.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut into squares.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; let cool.
Add flavor and Miracle Whip.
When well blended, stir in remaining ingredients. Pour in 1 quart mold or flat dish; refrigerate.
This salad is good with meat or fish.

title: cooked play dough for children
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it forms a ball.
Remove from heat and place on floured counter.
Knead until smooth.
Store in covered container.
Kids love it.

title: pot pie supreme
directions: Use a large casserole.
Cover the bottom with 1 can undiluted soup.
Add vegetables.
Add second can of soup; spread.
Add meat. Add third can of soup; spread over all.
Pour 1/2 cup of white wine and stir in gently.
Add herbs, thyme, basil, etc.
Cover all with a piece of puff pastry, thawed.
Pierce here and there.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
May be made ahead.
Serves 8.

title: sausage and beans
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onion, garlic and green pepper until slightly tender.
Slice all sausages and add to skillet.
Saute lightly.
Combine with all remaining ingredients in large roasting pan.
Stir.
Place in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttermilk refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine 6 cups of the flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in softened yeast.
Add buttermilk; stir until smooth.
If necessary, stir in enough of the remaining flour to make manageable dough.
Shape into a ball.
Place in greased bowl; turn once.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight or as long as five days. Grease baking sheets.
Shape dough as desired.
Brush with a little melted butter.
Let rise in warm place until double (1 to 3 hours).
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart saucepan, heat brown sugar, corn syrup, oleo, cream of tartar and salt to boiling to 260°.
Cook 5 minutes or more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda thoroughly and pour over popped corn.
Stir gently.
Bake in a preheated oven at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir 2 or 3 times.
Put on waxed paper.

title: round steak with tomato sauce
directions: Cut round steak in 3 x 3-inch pieces; brown in 1/4 cup of oil. Add tomato sauce, garlic powder and salt; simmer 20 minutes, then serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and refrigerate overnight or for several hours, so they won't be mushy when diced.
Chop bell pepper and pickle in small pieces.
Add to potatoes along with the pimentos; add mayonnaise and salt, if desired.

title: sumi salad(slaw)
directions: Spread almonds and sesame seed evenly on baking sheet with sides.
Toast in a 325° oven for 6 to 8 minutes, or until fragrant.
Cool.
Cook chicken breast ahead of time.
Remove from bone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Shred or thinly slice head of cabbage.
Add onions, chicken breast and Ramen noodles, broken into pieces.

title: chess pies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked deep dish pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Chill before serving, preferably overnight.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and line with graham crackers (not crushed).
Make pudding, using milk, and blend in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers.
Make another layer of crackers and then pudding.
End with crackers on top layer.

title: cranberry baked beans
directions: Place Beans in a dutch oven or soup kettle; add water to cover by 2 inches.
Bring to boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain Beans and discard liquid. Return Beans to dutch oven.
Add Cranberry Juice; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until the beans are almost tender.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in an 8-inch square pan.
Cream butter and 3/4 cup sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Spoon mixture over fruit.

title: creamy chocolate mousse
directions: Beat egg yolks lightly.
Add vanilla and melted chocolate to egg yolks, stirring well.
Beat egg whites at room temperature. Add cream of tartar at high speed until frothy.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form and sugar dissolves (2 to 4 minutes).
Stir about 1/4 of meringue into chocolate mixture; fold remainder of meringue into chocolate mixture.
Beat whipping cream at medium speed with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Fold cream into chocolate mixture.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Yields 5 cups.

title: turketts
directions: Combine turkey, 3/4 cup cheese, celery, olives and salt.
Mix lightly.
Place 4 cups of bread crumbs in bottom of dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour over bread. Refrigerate overnight.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Place in baking pan, peaches and pears, hollow side up.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: heavenly honeydew pie
directions: Cut melon in half.
Remove seeds and rind.
Cut
a few thin melon slices for garnish.
Set aside.
Cut remaining melon into chunks.
Place melon chunks in food processor or blender.
Process until smooth.
(There should be 3 cups puree.)

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Wash and remove centers from peppers.
Place upright in a greased baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stuff into the peppers.
Cover and bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Uncover the last 15 minutes.

title: peggy's surprise pastries
directions: Roll slices of bread with rolling pin until very thin.
Trim off 3 crusts.
Spread bread slices with soft butter.
At the end where crust remains, place a teaspoon of jelly or preserves.
Roll up and spread top with butter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for approximately 15 minutes, then at 375° for 5 minutes more or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
When cooled, sift 10x sugar over top.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add all ingredients except 1 cup of pecans.
Shape into ball and roll in remaining pecans. Refrigerate overnight.

title: egg noodles and sauce
directions: Thinly dice onion and saute in butter.
Brown ground beef in sauteed onions; add tomato sauce and the rest of ingredients. Simmer until ready to serve.
Serve over noodles.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn and set aside.
Boil for 5 minutes the sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Add vanilla and baking soda. Stir in real good.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add whipped topping and salad dressing.
Mix well.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion in frying pan.
Cook until crisp. Drain.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cheddared venison stew(easy and one of the most tasty i've ever had!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat in vegetable oil.
Transfer meat to 2-quart casserole.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over meat.
Bake, covered, for 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chinese coleslaw
directions: Cook chicken; drain.
Cube chicken.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Do not cook the Ramen noodles, they will be softened.

title: cinnamon spread
directions: Mix together well and spread on toast or rolls.

title: peanut butter party mix
directions: Combine cereals, nuts and pretzels and pour into shallow pans. Combine butter, peanut butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over cereal mix and toss until evenly coated.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Cool on paper towels and store in airtight container.
(Good for goodie bags.)

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in mixture of flour, cream of tartar and soda.
Chill, covered, for several hours.
Shape into small balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: heart-healthy lemon pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl; mix well.
Beat at low speed until blended.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool in pan for 25 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put 7 broken candy bars in a large glass bowl.
Microwave until melted, stir them occasionally.
Takes about 3 to 5 minutes. Add 3/4 container of Cool Whip to the melted candy bars. Mix thoroughly.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with rest of candy bar.
Cool and serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon into plastic bag.
Shake 6 or 8 pieces of biscuit at a time in sugar mixture and arrange in a well-greased tube or Bundt pan until all biscuits are used.
Arrange nuts or raisins among the biscuits.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix pudding following package directions.
Pour into crust. Top with sliced banana and pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and cream in saucepan.
Mix well.
Add water and
egg.
Cook
over
slow heat until soft ball stage. Remove from
heat and add butter.	Add vanilla.
Beat about 2 minutes until nice and glossy.

title: barbecued steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except steak in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cut steak into thin slices and put in Pyrex 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour hot barbecue sauce over steak and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: peanut butter-chocolate pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 4 (3 1/2 cup) mini loaf pans.
Mix dry ingredients (except chips).
Beat butter, peanut butter and sugar until pale and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until blended.
Beat in buttermilk and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture until just blended; stir in chocolate chips.

title: peach pie
directions: Bake and cool pie shell, completely cooled. Let peaches, lemon juice and sugar stand until juice forms. Drain and save juice. If the drained juice is not enough to make a full cup, add enough 7-Up to make a full cup. Add juice and cornstarch. Cook until thick. Add butter and almond flavoring. Let completely cool before pouring over peaches. Pour into cold pie shell and top with Cool Whip.

title: favorite chocolate frosting
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Add milk and vanilla to cocoa. Mix and stir until smooth.
Add powdered sugar.
Will cover 9 x 13-inch cake or 2 layer cake.

title: chocolate pixies(club member: lee ann mcraney)
directions: In small saucepan over low heat, melt butter and chocolate; stir to blend. Cool. In large bowl, beat chocolate mixture, 1 cup of the flour, sugar, eggs, baking powder and salt until well mixed. Stir in remaining 1 cup flour and the nuts. Cover; refrigerate until firm, 2 hours or overnight. Shape teaspoons of dough into balls. Roll in powdered sugar. Bake in 300° oven 12 to 15 minutes or until firm to the touch. Cool on wire racks.

title: binger dessert
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and marshmallows.
Cook until dissolved, then add nuts, raisins, coconut and crushed wafers.
Pack into a container and refrigerate.
Unmold and serve in slices.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Wash and slice carrots.
Cook until tender.
Set aside and mix first three items and bring to boil.
Add sliced onions and bell pepper and cook for a short time, then add the can of soup.
Cook until onion and bell pepper are tender.
Add cooked carrots and bring to a boil.

title: microwave japanese steak
directions: Combine the soy sauce, lemon juice, sugar and cornstarch.
Add the beef strips and marinate for 20 minutes at room temperature. Combine the oil, garlic, onion and ginger in a pie plate and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Place the onion in the center of the dish and place the meat around the outside edge of the dish, reserving the marinade.
Microwave, covered, on High for 3 minutes. Stir the onion and the meat together.
Add the reserved marinade and the pepper strips.
Microwave, covered, on High for 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, eggs, cheese, onion, lemon juice and mushroom soup.
Pour over prepared spinach.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Top with bread crumbs or cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken in a garden
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Layer in the following order in a bowl the lettuce, pepper, celery, mushrooms, onions and peas.
In a separate bowl mix mayonnaise, sugar, garlic powder and basil.
Spread over the peas, then add the cheese.
Sprinkle the bacon on top of the cheese. Cover and refrigerate 4 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Use 1 1/2 packages chipped beef, cut in large squares, to pack around outside of ball.

title: aunt alberta's special punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aids, water, juices and sugar to taste.
Make it pretty sweet.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add about 1 or 2 quarts 7-Up or ginger ale to taste and 1/2 gallon sherbet.
I usually freeze some punch in a muffin tin to float in punch bowl to keep it cold.
Makes about 2 1/2 gallon of punch to serve about 36 people.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Cook onions and pepper until done in enough oil to keep from sticking.
Take onions and pepper out of skillet.
Put on serving dish. Sprinkle vinegar over chicken.
Cook chicken in same skillet until done.
Use just enough oil to keep from sticking.
Just cover skillet bottom.
When chicken is almost done, put onions and pepper back in skillet and cook 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Take up and serve.
Beef or pork may be substituted for chicken.

title: meat and vegetable pie
directions: In bottom crust, put layer of hamburger.
Next, put chopped onion on hamburger, some salt and pepper and diced potatoes.
Next layer can of drained peas and carrots.
On top of potatoes, add little more salt and pepper with 1 tablespoon margarine on top. Put on top crust.
Poke a few holes into top crust with fork. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Brown rice in oleo in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and put in casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, covered. Uncover. Stir and cook for an additional 30 minutes.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Arrange in a greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix in order given and chill.

title: potato onion casserole
directions: Select long casserole dish and butter.
Peel potatoes and onions.
Layer sliced potato, layer sliced onion rings, salt and pepper.
Layer again the sliced potatoes, onion rings, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
May add Parmesan cheese, if desired. Bake at 375° until potatoes are tender.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, vanilla, vinegar and water. Beat until smooth.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's last minute brownies
directions: Hand mix instant pudding and milk; add cake mix and blend thoroughly.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Top with chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Layer in casserole dish: potatoes, beans, ground beef, onion and tomato sauce, using a little in each layer until all ingredients are used.
Should be 2 more more layers of each.
Add salt and pepper.
Add water.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 375°.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour boiling water over dates, butter and baking soda.
Add flour, sugar, salt and remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: spicy pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl until oil is absorbed. Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given and bake in oven at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 medium size loaves.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes; mix all ingredients together and place in buttered dish.
Cover with topping.

title: pumpkin and cream cheese roll-up
directions: Preheat over to 375°.
Grease 15x10x1-inch jelly roll pan. Line with wax paper.
Grease and flour wax paper.

title: spicy peanut butter chicken
directions: Remove skin and bone from chicken; discard.
Pull meat apart to have small pieces.
Do not cut up meat.
Puree whole contents of can of tomatoes.
Put chicken, tomatoes, onion, El Pato sauce, pepper, salt and basil in a large frying pan.
Simmer until onions are tender.
Stir in peanut butter.
Simmer until thick (about 20 minutes).
Serve as burros, over rice.

title: baked fish with cornbread stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut partially thawed fish into 4 portions.
In medium saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Add onion and celery and saute.
Add water and contents of vegetable seasoning packet from stuffing mix package.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in stuffing mix. Cover and let stand 5 minutes, then stir in 1/4 cup mayonnaise. Spoon dressing into individual oven-proof dishes or shallow 1-quart casserole.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Cook all ingredients on medium heat until water cooks out and mixture looks grainy.
Place on cookie sheet, spread in a single layer.
Bake at 325° until lightly brown.
Check nuts often, they will burn quickly.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Rinse lettuce; drain.
Break up lettuce into small pieces. Put in bottom 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chop up green pepper and onion and sprinkle over lettuce.
Mix in bowl the frozen peas, Worcestershire sauce and enough mayo to generously coat peas (need enough to make salad moist).
Spread peas over lettuce, onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle cheese over pea mixture.
Crumble bacon over cheese for last layer.

title: garden delight pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pizza mix according to package directions. Cover with pizza topping. Sprinkle remaining ingredients on top.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: dip for nacho (tortilla) chips
directions: Spread refried beans in the bottom of a baking (flat) dish. (Can warm beans in microwave before spreading out in pan.)
Layer the remaining ingredients over the beans.
Lettuce may be added, if desired.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream sugar, margarine and pudding mix.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour mixture.
Beat well. Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden.

title: down home sweet potatoes
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan with tight fitting lid, place the potatoes and mix with the remaining ingredients until potatoes are coated. Cook with lid for approximately 1/2 hour or until soft. This will make its own sauce.

title: bul's dip
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add chopped chilies or jalapenos (the more you use, the spicier it will be).
Put tomatoes in a colander and squeeze them dry.
Then add to onion and chilies.
Slowly, add grated cheese, stirring constantly, until melted.
Add salt to taste.
Serve warm with chips.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: In a bowl, stir together flour, brown sugar, walnuts and oleo. Spread evenly in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from oven.
Cool.

title: zucchini with baby carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients, except zucchini, in a large skillet. Cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add zucchini. Cover and cook 3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Add additional water, one tablespoon at a time, if necessary, to prevent sticking.
Yields 6 servings.

title: tuna log
directions: Mix together; chill and roll into log.
Sprinkle with crushed pecans.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix as directed on package, but replace 1/3 cup of water with 1/3 cup green creme de menthe.
Bake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Upon removal from oven, spread with the fudge topping.
Cool.
While cooling, mix the Cool Whip with 1/3 cup green creme de menthe.
Spread on cooled cake and refrigerate.
Flavor is better after at least 8 hours in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Take one box yellow cake mix.
Remove one cup for crumb topping.
To remainder of cake mix, add melted butter and 1 beaten egg.
Mix with flour until cake mix is absorbed.
Press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring broth to boil.
Add soy sauce, lemon juice and sesame oil.
Lower heat; simmer for 5 minutes.
Drizzle egg into soup in a steady stream.
Wait a few moments for the egg to set before stirring.
Stir and serve.
Serves 4.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and bananas and mix well. Add baking soda, flour and nuts, if desired, and mix well.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix in blender all of the ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Then bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Center of pie should be set.

title: grandmom's chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together well butter, sugar and cocoa.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 400° then 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: never fail pie dough
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg, water and vinegar.
Blend into dry ingredients.
Form into ball.
Divide into thirds.
Roll out on floured board.
Will keep in refrigerator.
Yields 3 crusts.

title: anderson beet salad
directions: Open and drain beets.
Discard liquid.
Cut up onion fine. Add onion, vinegar, sugar, Miracle Whip, salt and pepper to beets. Add more sugar, if needed. Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Cut lettuce and add 1 hour before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: devil's food-cocoa cake
directions: Add all ingredients in order.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and mix well. Cream butter and sugar thoroughly. Beat in eggs; stir in soaked oatmeal. Sift flour and remaining dry ingredients. Stir into oatmeal mixture. Pat into 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in pan. Spread with topping. Broil until golden, about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown the bacon, drain and cut into snippets (small pieces). Saute the veggies in some of the bacon grease.
Add rice and saute until veggies are somewhat crispy.
Add tomatoes, soup and bacon pieces.
Cook in heavy pan, about 1 hour, on top of stove.
Stir to keep from sticking.
May need a little moisture added.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze liquid out of spinach.
Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and croutons.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and croutons. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese. Add all ingredients; roll in ball. Roll ball in pecans.

title: spicy vegetable chili
directions: Heat oil.
Add onions and garlic.
Add zucchini, red pepper and jalapenos and cook for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer.
Serve with grated Jack cheese and cilantro.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Peel
green skin away from rind.
Leave a little of the pink portion
for
a
touch of pink; makes a prettier pickle. Cut
into squares or fancy shapes.
Dissolve salt in 1 gallon cold
water and
pour
over
prepared
rind.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Stir alum in 2 gallons water
and add to rinds;
bring to a	boil.
Reduce
heat
and simmer 30 minutes. Drain and rinse.
Add
another
gallon
of water and simmer until tender but not soft,
30 to 45 minutes. Heat vinegar, 3 cups water and sugar to a boil.
Tie spices in a bag and add with rind.
Cook slowly, uncovered, until syrup is	thickened, about 1 hour.
Pack hot
into	hot
sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: taco supreme
directions: Brown hamburger; drain the grease.
Add 1/2 package taco seasoning and 1/2 the water required for seasoning directions. Simmer until the juice is gone.
Mix in the beans, cheeses and hot peppers.
Spread on a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until the cheese melts.

title: fresh rhubarb pie
directions: Pour into pastry lined pie plate; dot with butter.
Cover with lattice top crust.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° until juice begins to bubble through and crust is light brown.
Serve warm.

title: camaron ala embotido(roll-up shrimp filipino style)
directions: Skin shrimp with tail on.
Part the shrimp at the back, not cutting through.
Slice pork equal length with the shrimp, so with celery and sausage.
Marinate pork and shrimp with the soy sauce. Place shrimp on the wrap; stuff with the pork, sausage and celery. Roll and wrap.
Seal wrap with egg white.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: "better than sex" cake
directions: Bake cake in large dish.
Poke holes in it.
Add sugar to pineapple and heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cake.
Top with pudding prepared according to directions.
Top pudding with Cool Whip and then coconut.

title: tiffany inspired rice pudding
directions: Bring rice, salt and water to boil; add milk, salt, sugar and cornstarch.
Mix and cook for 2 minutes.
Add egg yolks, slightly beaten.
Blend a little of the custard with the egg yolks, and then add to the custard and cook another minute stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter and place in a baking dish.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar and fold whites into custard mixture.
Brown in a 350° oven.

title: old settlers' baked beans
directions: Brown meats and onions; drain and mix.
Combine brown sugar, granulated sugar, catsup, dry mustard and molasses; add to meat mixture.
Add beans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: swiss steak (crock-pot)
directions: Place round steak in crock-pot.
Add soups and water; spread over meat.
Salt and pepper.
Cook on high for 5 hours.

title: orange balls
directions: Use a rolling pin to crush the vanilla wafers in a plastic bag. Mix the softened margarine with the crushed vanilla wafers. Add the powdered sugar and the orange juice. Stir until well mixed. Form the mixture into balls and then roll in the powdered sugar or coconut.

title: thick roquefort salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend with beater or blender.
Put in covered jar and refrigerate.
Chill and use within a day or two. Makes 1 pint.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in skillet. Drain off fat. Add barbecue sauce and stir. Pile it on a hamburger bun.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan; stir in water.
Boil for 1 minute; stir constantly.
Add fruit; pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish or 9-inch pie pan.
Top with the oil and cinnamon.

title: coconut custard
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add melted butter, milk and flavoring.
Add pinch of salt and mix well.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in oven at 375°.
Use 2 or 3 pie shells.

title: strawberry candy
directions: Mix dry Jell-O, milk and coconut slowly.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator for 4 hours. Shape into strawberries and then roll in sugar.
Add green almond for stem.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix and serve. Fast and delicious.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan with no-stick cooking spray.
Pour pineapple juice over each piece of chicken and sprinkle each piece with lemon pepper.
Cook about 1 hour.

title: corn and sausage casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion separately.
Add onion and beaten eggs to corn.
Alternate corn and meat in casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: basic victoria sandwich cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and creamy in texture. Add eggs, a little at a time, carefully stir in flour.
Bake in a 7-inch cake tin for approximately 35 minutes at 325°.
When cool, split and fill with jam or cream.

title: swedish kringle
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients as for pie crust.
Pat on a cookie sheet in two long strips about 3-inches wide.
Place the 1 cup water and butter in a pan and heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and add the 1 cup flour and then the eggs, beating after each addition.
Add the almond flavoring.
Spread lightly on top of the pie crust mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
When cool, frost with Buttercream Frosting.
One recipe of frosting is enough for 3 or 4 recipes of Kringle.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop onion and garlic and saute in 3 to 4 tablespoons olive oil about 3 to 7 minutes. Add tomatoes, puree, paste and spices (including salt and pepper). Add water; stir until well blended and put on low heat to cook all day. Stir often and taste often.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar.
Beat
in egg yolks.	Stir in jam. Sift
flour
with
all
the
dry ingredients.
Add flour mixture in	about
three
parts, alternately with sour cream. Beat after each addition until blended.
Pour into 3 cake pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: filled berlin doughnuts
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Put 1/2 cup sugar, salt, butter, orange juice and rum extract into a large bowl.
Pour scalded milk over ingredients in bowl.
Stir until butter is melted.
Cool to lukewarm.
Blend in 1 cup of the flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in yeast.
Add about half of the remaining flour and beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs, then beat in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: yellow cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix in another bowl the milk, egg and oil.
Add milk mixture to cornmeal mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking pan until half full.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ultimate vegetarian chili
directions: In small saucepan bring water to a boil.
Add bulgur and turn heat to low.
Simmer, covered, about 15 minutes until water is absorbed.
In large soup pot, heat oil.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic.
Saute about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add spices, mixing well.
Add tomatoes with juice, chopping them in the pot.
Stir in kidney beans and cooked bulgur.
Simmer on low heat, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until
heated through.
Serve topped with shredded cheese if desired.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: success in a skillet
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon and onions until transparent.
Add lunch meat.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two large greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans. Mix up and pat out in baking dish (like a crust).
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Whip the cream cheese and sugar until fluffy and soft.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip and mix.
Spread on top of crust.

title: cheesy corn bake
directions: Melt butter or margarine with cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in a 2-quart baking dish, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir and let set until cool.
Add oil to raisin mixture.
Combine flour, sugar and spices.
Add this and nuts to raisin mixture.
Mix well.
Grease 3 (46 ounce) cans or 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Add dough to pans and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Combine butter, cocoa and buttermilk.
Bring to a boil and add powdered sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Add vanilla, salt and pecans. Spread over brownies.

title: minestrone
directions: Slice sausage in 1/2-inch rings and brown in oil.
Add onion and carrot and cook 5 minutes more.
Add bouillon and remaining ingredients except beans.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add beans and cook 20 minutes more.
Put in 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/4 teaspoon pepper during the last 20 minutes of cooking.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Cream together sugar and oleo.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Add almond extract. Pour half of batter in pan; cover with half of cranberry sauce. Pour in rest of batter.
Cover with remaining cranberry sauce and nuts.
Bake for 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat egg whites, blend in sugar.
Cook rice about 2 minutes. Mix all other ingredients together.
Blend in egg whites to mixture while hot.
Place mixture in baking dish.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cool and serve.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Bring milk and butter to a boil.
Mix flour, 1 cup at a time, to eggs and sugar.
Add milk and butter; beat, then add salt, vanilla and baking powder.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: sweet pickle quarters
directions: Use small pickling cucumbers and quarter them lengthwise. Slowly pour boiling water over the cucumbers to cover.
Let stand for two hours, then drain.
Pack into hot, half-pint jars that have been prepared according to the manufacturer's instructions. Jars can be filled to within 1/4-inch of the top.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Beat in a large mixing bowl for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cut up apples into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with mixture of the remaining ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and red-eye gravy
directions: Fry ham slices slowly and be careful not to overcook.
Remove from pan.
Make gravy in pan the ham was fried in.
Pour in a small amount of coffee, right from the pot.
Add a little water and bring to a boil.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook until tender the rice in 2 cups salted water while frying bacon (chopped) until crisp.
Add hamburger (salt and pepper to taste) and onion (chopped).
Cook until done and drain grease. Combine with rice and paprika.
Stir in tomatoes.
Use a large bowl that can be used in oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Pour into 2 well-buttered pie pans (no crust).
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: salsa picante
directions: Place tomatoes, onion, garlic and jalapenos in a food processor.
Blend to desired consistency.
Heat oil in a saucepan, add tomato mixture and Mexican herb mix.
Bring to a boil, decrease temperature and cook gently for 10 minutes.
Allow salsa to cool.
Pour into glass jars and refrigerate until ready to use. Keeps one month.

title: fire hot grits
directions: Cook grits.
Mix in other ingredients.
Bake in a large, greased casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: treasured gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in oleo. Reserve 1 cup of this mixture for topping.
Add cinnamon, soda, nutmeg and ginger to remaining flour mixture.
Stir in eggs and buttermilk.
(Do not use electric mixer.)
Pour batter into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the reserved topping over batter and bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients. Add last four. Mix and pour into 3 round sprayed cake pans and cook for 30 minutes on 300 degrees.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and cottage cheese; add remaining ingredients. Save a few orange pieces to decorate top.

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: Cook noodles by directions on package.
Brown 1 pound hamburg. Cover bottom of pan (13 x 9-inch oblong) with sauce.
Add 1/2 noodles, Mozzarella and Ricotta cheese; sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Add meat.
Cover with sauce.
Add remaining noodles, cheese, meat and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, uncovered, and 20 minutes, covered.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pineapple and cherry pie filling into pan.
Sprinkle with cake mix evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts. Slice margarine over top evenly.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, 4 1/2 tablespoons sugar and butter. Pat into a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir until completely dissolved.
Add sugar and pineapple juice and allow to cool. Soften cream cheese and gradually stir in gelatin mixture until well blended.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate until firmly set.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: shrimp curry rice
directions: Combine onion, vinegar, oil and curry powder in a bowl.
Stir in rice and chill 2 hours to blend flavors.
Just before serving, add celery, green pepper, shrimp and mayonnaise (cut shrimp in desired pieces).
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix together the above ingredients and chill until time to serve.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat ingredients for 5 minutes.
Divide into 3 cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan, oiled and floured.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: special chicken
directions: Place boneless chicken on bottom of Corning Ware dish.
Place 1 slice of cheese over each chicken breast.
Spread mushroom and celery soup over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Put cherry pie filling in bottom of 8-inch square cake pan. Mix oats, brown sugar and flour with butter.
Sprinkle over cherry filling; add nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef in mushroom and red wine sauce
directions: Season; marinate or tenderize beef to taste (if desired). Place beef and all other ingredients into crock-pot and stir; mix well.
Cook on high for 5 to 6 hours or until beef is cooked to your preference.
Serve over buttered noodles, rice, pasta or mashed potatoes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Drop on cookie sheet and brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Dice apples (with or without peelings) in greased baking dish. Pour slightly beaten eggs over apples.
Combine the rest of the ingredients separately and pour over apples and eggs.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and garlic spread
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons olive oil, garlic and red pepper flakes in a small skillet.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until garlic begins to sizzle.
Remove from heat.
Place a vegetable steamer over 1 inch of water in a medium size saucepan.
Add potato; cover and steam until almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Add broccoli and salt; cover and steam until broccoli and potato are tender, about 5 minutes more.

title: chicken  fried steak
directions: Combine egg and water. Dip steak in egg and water mixture. Roll in flour and brown on both sides. Cover and cook for 30 minutes on low heat. Remove meat from cooking pan. Put rest of seasonings and 1 c. of flour to pan and stir until brown. Add milk, stirring until thickened. Boil 2 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat the oil and eggs until you have a "frothy" mixture.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add the flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Fold in the apples.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey piccata
directions: Pound each turkey cutlet into 1/8-inch thickness; set aside. In pie plate with fork, beat eggs with milk until well blended. On waxed paper, place bread crumbs.
Dip cutlets in egg mixture, then in crumbs, to coat on both sides.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot butter or margarine, cook turkey cutlets until browned on both sides, adding more butter or margarine if necessary.
With slotted pancake turner, remove cutlets to plate; keep warm.
Reduce heat to low.
Squeeze juice of 1 lemon (or to suit taste) into drippings in skillet; stir in water, chicken flavor bouillon and salt until well mixed, scraping to loosen brown bits from bottom.
Return turkey cutlets to skillet; cover and simmer mixture 15 minutes or until cutlets are fork-tender.

title: easy black beans and yellow rice
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan and saute onion until soft.
Add 1 can undrained black beans and heat through on low heat.
Mash beans with a potato masher to make a thick mixture.
Add remaining cans of undrained beans and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook the yellow rice according to package directions and serve the beans over the hot rice.

title: california overnight yeast rolls
directions: Mix together: let sit 30 minutes: 1 cake yeast pack, sugar, and milk. Add: eggs, salt, flour, and butter. Let stand overnight without refrigeration. Next morning, cut dough into fourths and roll to size of 9 inch pan-1/2 inch thick. Cut pie into 8 wedges. Roll large end to small. Place on well greased cookie sheets. Let stand until ready to bake (can wait 8-12 hours). Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Brush with melted butter when removed from oven.

title: penne pasta with vodka tomato sauce
directions: Combine olive oil, garlic and pepper. Cook over moderate heat until garlic is lightly golden. Stir in tomatoes and simmer 15 minutes. Add cooked pasta to tomato sauce. Add vodka. Reduce heat to low and add cream. Cook for 2 minutes and serve topped with parsley.

title: nita's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon or ham.
Bake, covered, 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove.
Top with bacon or ham.
Return, uncovered, until bacon or ham is brown.
Serves 50.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 1 hour in greased Bundt pan.

title: candied carrots
directions: Cut carrots in 2-inch pieces or in thick slices.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in medium-sized pan.
Cover; cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Uncover and cook until heavy syrup is formed.
Be careful not to burn.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until done; drain.
Spray dish and place broccoli on bottom, then chicken.
Combine soup, lemon juice and mayo in a bowl and microwave until partly warm.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
(Loosen so soup can go down through.)
Top with bread crumbs and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake 35 minutes until bubbly at 350°.
(Cover and take off for last 15 minutes.)
Serve over rice.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn flakes.
Melt on low heat until melted, then on high until it comes to a full boil.
Add crushed corn flakes.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Wash and drain chicken.
Put chicken in roasting bag and place in oblong baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken and seal bag.
Cut 3 small slits in bag and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: green beans
directions: Open beans; drain water off.
Put about 1 cup water, butter and dash of salt and pepper and cook until tender or until water is gone.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted. Cook over low heat for 3 minutes after melted, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal.
Using waxed paper, press mixture evenly into a buttered pan.
Cut when cool.
Yield: 24 squares, 2 x 2 inches.

title: overnight salad
directions: Mix jello, pineapple
and sugar all together.
Let come to a boil.
Chill
until thickened.
Add marshmallows, coconut and whipped cream or
Cool
Whip.
Mix together and let chill. Top with nuts, if desired.

title: hamburger tater tot casserole
directions: Put hamburg raw or cooked on bottom of 1-quart casserole.
Add onions, mushrooms and green pepper (if wanted).
Pour soup over top.
Pour Tater Tops over top.
Cook 1 hour.
May freeze it ahead.
Good if some frozen peas are added.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Mix noodles in ground beef.
Add both cans of soup. Pour into casserole dish.
Add grated cheese and heat in oven at 350° until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, molasses and vinegar or lemon juice.
Sift together flour, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add soda to cup of hot coffee and add alternately with flour and creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on greased pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit cake bars
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; cover and set aside for 24 hours. Add next 2 ingredients and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and spread in a greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch cookie pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut.
Will keep 3 weeks if stored in airtight container and kept at room temperature.
These freeze well also.
If you like fruit cake, you'll love these.

title: dump cake
