directions: Into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan, dump 2 cans pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix over filling.
Slice margarine over cake mix to dot.
Sprinkle with pecans and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: old timey sweet potato pie
directions: Put into bottom of 1 pie shell the sweet potatoes.
Add butter on top.
Sprinkle cinnamon, white sugar and water on butter, then put on top layer crust.
Bake 1 hour, until brown, at 350°.
Put holes in top crust.

title: white mountain frosting
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a small saucepan. Cover and place over moderate heat (about 250°) until mixture just starts to boil.
Uncover and boil rapidly without stirring until candy thermometer registers 242°, or until a small amount of mixture spins a 6 to 8-inch thread.
As mixture boils, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Gradually pour in hot syrup in a thin stream.
Beat at medium speed until all syrup is added.
Add vanilla; continue beating at high speed until stiff peaks form. Makes enough frosting for two round 8 or 9-inch layer cake or one 9 x 11 x 1/2-inch cake.

title: easy crisp sweet pickles
directions: Cut pickles crossways (chunks) and put	in
large bowl. Combine sugar and water.
Bring to a boil in
small pan.
Stir constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add celery seed.
Add a few drops green food
coloring	to
syrup. Pour syrup over cut pickles.
Let stand
at
room
temperature for about
hours,
stirring every 1/2 hour.	Pour back into pickle jar and refrigerate.
The longer these set the crispier they get.

title: double layer banana split
directions: Peel and cut bananas lengthwise in a bowl. Add 3 scoops of ice cream. Slice the bananas on top of ice cream. Put 3 scoops of ice cream, then an extra scoop in center with cherry on top.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix slightly beaten eggs, and add sugar, salt and milk. Add vanilla
and
nutmeg,
if desired.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and
bake
at
until crust begins to brown.
Then reduce heat
to
and
bake custard until firm, about 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar; add pumpkin, water, oil, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and beat well. Add flour slowly, beat well. Add raisins and nuts, blend well with spoon. Pour into 4 greased and floured loaf pans, filling each 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Delicious served warm with butter. May be frozen after cooling.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour, potato chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheets.
Grease bottom of glass and dip into sugar and use to flatten dough.
Top with nut and bake for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Fry hamburger and drain grease. Combine rest in Dutch kettle on the stove and heat to boiling, then cover pan and simmer for 30 minutes. Take out bay leaf before serving.

title: peach preserves
directions: Combine the peaches and the sugar and let stand in a cool place overnight.
Boil gently, stirring frequently, until the fruit is clear and the syrup thick, about 45 minutes.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: cinnamon-raisin bread
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt in a small saucepan; heat until shortening melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; beat in eggs and milk mixture.
Beat in 4 cups of flour until smooth.
Stir in raisins; add enough more flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place in large greased bowl, turning once to coat with shortening.
Cover and allow to rise in a warm place until double in bulk.

title: golden velvet chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in shallow baking dish.
Place 1/2 slice cheese on each breast.
Mix soup, juice, mayo and wine.
Pour this over cheese and sprinkle all with crushed croutons.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: deviled egg mold
directions: Sprinkle
gelatine
on water to soften.
Place over low heat and
stir
until gelatine is dissolved.
Remove from heat and
add salt, lemon
juice, Worcestershire sauce and cayenne pepper. Cool.
Stir
in mayonnaise.
Fold in remaining.
Turn into a
3 cup
mold or individual molds and chill until firm. Unmold by dipping
mold
in
warm
water.
Garnish with salad greens and green pepper or parsley.

title: sandy's potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes or leave skins on.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch cubes. Parboil until edges are transparent.
(Do not overcook.)
Drain. While still hot pour into a large casserole.
Add onions (chopped), Velveeta (cubed), bacon bits, mayo, salt and pepper; mix well. Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
(You can cook right away, but not as good.)
Uncover and cook at 375° for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.
(Do not stir while baking.)
Everything will melt together near the end.

title: peanut butter extras
directions: Heat sugar and syrup in a big saucepan on medium heat.
At the first boil (it will foam up) quickly add peanut butter, then cereal.
Stir.
Turn fire off and spoon on greased foil.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: With meat hammer, pound breasts several times.
Beat egg and small amount of milk.
Put flour in one bowl and bread crumbs in another.
Place 1 slice ham and 1 slice cheese on each breast. Roll and secure with toothpick.
Roll first in flour, then egg, then bread crumbs, coating well.
Fry in oil until crisp.
Place in baking dish; add chicken broth to cover bottom.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Remove skin, rinse and pat dry.
In a plastic bag, combine Parmesan cheese, flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Slightly whip egg whites and milk.
Add Tabasco if you like.
Dip chicken into egg mixture.
Place pieces in plastic bag, close and shake to coat chicken.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Delicious served with wild rice or fettucini noodles.
Serves 4. 230 calories.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease shallow casserole dish.
Layer in this order:
cracker crumbs, well drained asparagus and mushroom soup.
Use a teaspoon and just spoon about; do not smooth out and leave in little heaps. Add grated cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Place another layer of cracker crumbs and pour milk over all, almost to the top of the dish.
Sprinkle with almonds, if desired.
Bake at 350° until bubbly hot.

title: grandma's beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge steaks well with flour.
Brown floured steaks in butter.
Add onions (or onion soup), mushrooms, beef bouillon and water to cover.
Add wine and cook over low heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Fold in sour cream just before serving.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set overnight and serve.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Combine. Bring to a hard boil and pour over first 4 ingredients. Stir occasionally to be sure all cabbage is covered with vinegar. Store at least overnight in covered container in refrigerator. Keeps indefinitely.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix and spoon over peaches. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat 2 inches of oil to 375°.
Mix corn meal, flour, baking powder, soda, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs and buttermilk and add to dry ingredients.
Blend in onions.
Drop by tablespoon in hot oil and fry until golden brown.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Soft scramble in butter.
Mix soup and sherry.
Heat.

title: apples and cream cake
directions: Soften oleo; mix with dry yellow cake mix and chopped pecans. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour over top 1 can of pie filling. Sprinkle over top of this a mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Beat 1 egg and 1 cup sour cream; spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sesame salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir.
Pour on salad over Chinese cabbage.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Add scalded milk. Scald means to heat milk just to the boiling point, but do not allow to boil.
The pan used for scalding is easier to clean if rinsed out with hot water before adding milk.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Set aside 1/4 cup of walnuts for topping.
Mix all pie ingredients together and pour into a baked pie shell of your choice or into a prepared graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.

title: quick meat pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except pie crust.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pie crust according to package directions.
Roll out to fit 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until crust is golden brown.

title: apricot cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and turn into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Press ground beef into bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with evaporated milk, salt and pepper. Layer potatoes, onion, soup and cheese over top. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy quiche
directions: Blend all together.
Take whatever you like:
ham, onions, peppers, spinach, etc.
Fry up in pan.
Cook slightly.
Add your seasoning, salt and pepper.
Pour into pie crust.
Add Swiss cheese or Mozzarella.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375° uncovered until golden or until knife comes out clean.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet and bake until golden brown, approximately 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chocolate peanut butter ritz
directions: Make sandwich with crackers and peanut butter.
Melt almond bark according to package directions.
Dip crackers into chocolate and put on wax paper to harden.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients for crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in a glass 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cool.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil for 1 minute the margarine, cocoa, milk and sugar. Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in the peanut butter, oats and coconut.
When thoroughly mixed, drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper to cool.

title: quiche
directions: (You can add mushrooms, green peppers, etc., if you like.)

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix all together well.
Roll out and use cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Decorate with frosting and colored sugars.

title: pecan logs
directions: Cream together.
Roll into 8 logs about 4 inches long and 1 inch wide.
Put in freezer overnight.
Must be frozen solid. Melt 1 pound package of caramels in a double boiler.
Remove 1 log roll from freezer at a time.
Cover with caramel and place whole pecans on it.
Cover entirely with pecans.
It is easier to do 1/2 of log completely, then do other end.
When caramel is set, roll in plastic wrap and put in covered can.
Can be stored 1 to 2 months.

title: sausage omelette for a crowd
directions: Serve at breakfast with scrambled eggs, gravy, peach jelly, milk, coffee and juice, 1/2 wild turkey breast, cut into small thin strips.
Season with Lawry's seasoned salt and pepper.
Very little salt, but lots of pepper.
Flour turkey in Ziploc bag. Place turkey in bowl of milk.
Flour turkey again in Ziploc bag. Fry at 380° until golden brown.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and Karo syrup until ball forms from a drop in very cold water.
Ball should be very hard, then pour over egg whites that have been beaten to form peaks.
Beat mixture until it is hard to turn (when candy isn't glossy).
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour onto buttered platter or cookie sheet.
Spread evenly with a knife and chill.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 250°, stirring occasionally.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Yields 5 pints.

title: yaeger snitzel
directions: Dip steaks in egg, then into bread crumbs to coat.
Heat frying pan; melt 2 to 3 teaspoons butter in pan.
Once butter is almost melted, add a little oil to keep the batter from burning. Then fry meat (be careful as the meat will fry very quickly).

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil, vinegar, water and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Fold into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: caramel squares
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage, crumbled.
Put layer of bread cubes in bottom of dish.
Cover with layer of sausage; continue alternating layers, ending with sausage.
Mix grated cheese, eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Mix well and pour over sausage and bread.
Let mixture set overnight in refrigerator, covered.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 45 minutes in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Can be doubled.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into pie shell; chill until firm. Ready to serve.

title: date and orange slice bars
directions: Combine dates, sugar and 2 tablespoons flour in saucepan.
Boil until thick.
Cool.
Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs, add soda in hot water.
Blend in vanilla.
Stir in 1 3/4 cups sifted flour.
Add salt to taste and nuts.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with orange slices, cut lengthwise in thirds.
Spread date mixture over orange slices and top with remaining batter.
Bake, cool and cut in bars.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell; dot with butter.
Add top pastry crust.
Press edges together.
Cut small slits for steam to escape. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 50 minutes.

title: crazy or whacky cake
directions: In 9
x 11-inch cake pan stir dry ingredients together. Make 3 holes in mix and add oil in one, vinegar in another and vanilla in another.
Pour
water
over
all and stir a little. Don't overmix. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: chicken bake
directions: Spray large pan heavily with Pam.
Put in chicken pieces.
Put Swiss cheese over all the chicken.
Mix each can of soup with 3/4 cup of water.
Pour soup over all.
Sprinkle dry dressing on top. Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 2 hours.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except ketchup and honey and mix well.
Turn mixture into a 7 or 8-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until firm and brown on top. Combine ketchup and honey.
Spread evenly over top of loaf and bake 5 minutes longer.
If desired, serve with no-salt ketchup.
Yields 6 servings.

title: baked asparagus
directions: Combine all ingredients, except melted margarine, and put in a greased baking dish.
Pour half of the melted margarine over top of casserole.
Put uncovered dish in oven and bake about 15 minutes at 350°.
Pour remainder of margarine over casserole and finish baking until mixture is firm (approximately 30 minutes).

title: coconut pudding
directions: To make the pudding:
In a medium, heavy saucepan, combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, milk, egg yolks and flour.
Whisk together until smooth.
Place over medium heat and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter and stir well.
Line a 1 1/2-quart baking dish with half the vanilla wafers; top with half the coconut.
Pour half the custard on top of that.
Repeat all three layers.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Crush 1 roll of Ritz crackers fine and sprinkle on top.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and sour cream, mixing well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and nutmeg; add to batter and mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13X9X2 inch baking pan.
Combine brown sugar, pecan and cinnamon, mix well and sprinkle evenly over batter. Cover and chill overnight; uncover and bake at 350° F. for 35 - 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Makes 15 servings.
(Note: For a truly deluxe coffee cake, increase topping mixture to 1 cup of brown sugar and 1 cup of pecans.
Cinnamon stays the same.)

title: comforting cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a very large mixing bowl, combine oil, eggs and vanilla. Add sugar; mix well. In a separate bowl, combine flour, soda and salt. Add to sugar mixture, beating until blended. Stir in corn flakes, oats, chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by tablespoonfuls 3-inches apart onto a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake until light brown, 9 to 10 minutes. Cool slightly on cookie sheet and remove to wire rack to cool completely. Yield: 9 dozen.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon together and set aside. In saucepan, mix water, oleo, oil and cocoa.
Heat to boiling, then remove from heat.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla to flour mixture, then add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter, shortening, sugar and eggs; add flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not brown cookies.
Makes 6 dozen.
Can use colored sugar crystals for Christmas decor.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Mash potatoes; add melted butter, salt and orange juice; beat until light and fluffy.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all together; cook for 1 1/2 hours or until cooked up.

title: chocolate-caramel oatmeal bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine 2 cups flour, oats, brown sugar, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add margarine and beat at low speed of an electric mixer until mixture is crumbly.
Press half of mixture in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
(Reserve remaining crumb mixture.)
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.

title: buckeyes
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Make small bite-size balls.
Lay on wax paper and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: lasagne with vegetables and white sauce
directions: Make Parmesan cream sauce first. In saucepan, melt butter over low heat; add flour, blending into a smooth paste. Add salt, nutmeg and pepper and blend well; cook 2 minutes or until bubbly. Over medium heat, stirring constantly, gradually add milk and cook until mixture boils and thickens. Reduce heat to low; simmer 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in Parmesan cheese. Remove from heat; set aside.

title: southside delight
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add in salsa and a little water to prevent burning and to thin salsa a little.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle cheese on top and let it melt in.
Enjoy using chips to help scoop it up.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in bottom of crust.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender, mixer or processor.
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Should be golden brown and knife inserted comes out clean.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Shred lettuce in large bowl.
Layer pepper, onion and peas on top of lettuce.
Spread Miracle Whip on top and seal.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Shake Parmesan cheese on top.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Keeps two days.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake covered for 4 hours at 275°. Pull meat apart.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns.

title: triple chocolate and vanilla cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and oleo.
Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk; add eggs, vanilla and flour.
Mix well.
Divide batter in half.
Add chocolate to 1/2 of batter; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan. Top evenly with vanilla batter.
Bake 50 minutes until center springs back when touched.
Cool.
Top with Chocolate Glaze.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Mix in order given. Roll in ball in hand. Place on cookie sheet. Bake 375° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: freezer corn
directions: Cut corn off ears.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in oven at 300° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool, package and freeze.

title: sauerbraten meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and milk.
Make meatballs and brown in melted butter in large skillet.
Mix remaining ingredients.
When meatballs are browned, stir in combined liquid ingredients.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.

title: fruit delight
directions: Dissolve jello as directed on package and chill.
Whip cream and sweeten to taste.
When jello begins to congeal, fold into cream with rotary beater.
Dice and mix marshmallows, pecans and fruit and fold into mixture.
Set in refrigerator to jell.

title: cashew roast
directions: Fry until just partially cooked the onion and celery.
Drain mushrooms, saving liquid.
Mix with onion and celery and add soup, liquid from mushrooms, adding enough water to make 1 cup, cashews and noodles.
Mix all together and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, pickles, almonds and grapes in a bowl. Combine mayonnaise, salt and cider vinegar.
Pour over chicken in bowl and toss well.
Chill.

title: shrimp and pasta salad
directions: Boil shrimp.
Break spaghetti up and cook.
Mix all ingredients.
Marinate in covered bowl overnight.

title: baked pork and vegetables
directions: 1 hour, 45 minutes before serving preheat oven to 350°.
Brown pork steak well on both sides.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, mix other ingredients.
Arrange pork steaks on top.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, cream cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper, butter and garlic powder.
Pour into a shallow baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: bruschetta
directions: Using the coarse side of a grater, grate tomatoes into a bowl. Discard remaining skin.
Add oil, salt, pepper, basil and olives. Mix. Grill bread until brown like Melba toast.
Before bread cools, rub garlic clove over the entire surface of one side.
Each slice should use 1/4 clove of garlic.
Just before serving, spoon tomato mixture over bread.
Serve in small batches.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together except crackers. Pour into buttered casserole dish. Put crushed crackers on top and cover with thin pats of butter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions on package.
Drain well.
Add onions, celery, cheese and mayonnaise.
Place in casserole dish.
Butter bread crumbs by melting butter and mixing with bread crumbs.
Top casserole with bread crumbs.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding shrimp last.
Chill. Make 1 day ahead of time to let flavors blend.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush wafers; cream butter.
Add sugar and eggs, 1 at a time. Add milk alternately with crushed wafers.
Add nuts and coconut. Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Turn oven off; leave cake in oven for 15 minutes more.
Take out and cool.

title: one egg cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add egg and beat.
Add milk and flour alternately, beat well.
Add vanilla.
Bake in loaf about 25 minutes.
Double recipe for 3 ten-inch layers.

title: crumb cake
directions: Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Prepare topping.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar in small bowl.
Add flour and walnuts mix to crumb mixture; save 1 c. for topping.
Press remainder into bottom of 8 x 8 pan.
Bake 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Set oven to 400°.
Butter large baking dish.
In a bowl, toss together rhubarb (cut into 1-inch chunks), lemon rind and juice, sugar, flour, nutmeg and butter (cut into tiny pieces).
Transfer this mixture to baking dish.
Cover with topping made by mixing together in a bowl and using a pastry blender, the flour, cut up unsalted butter, brown sugar, spices and oatmeal.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until mixture is bubbling and top is golden brown.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix together Tang, sour cream, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip in a large bowl.
When smooth, pour into pie crust.
Decorate with drained oranges.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in microwave. Mix all other ingredients well. Add to cheese. Mix well.

title: party meatballs
directions: Make bite size meatballs and brown in small amount of shortening.
Drain well.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: To a half pint of grated horseradish, add 2 teaspoons of made mustard, sugar, salt and vinegar.
Serve with beef or other meats.

title: butterfingers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease shallow baking pan, about 8 x 12-inches.
Cream butter, sugar and lemon rind thoroughly.
Beat in egg.
Fold in flour.
Spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: melt-away cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in flour and cornstarch.
Wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Make into small balls.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely, then glaze.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: eclair cake
directions: In a 12 x 15-inch pan, place a layer of graham crackers on bottom of pan.
Mix pudding, 5 cups milk and Cool Whip.
Pour mixture over crackers. Layer crackers evenly on top of mixture. Melt chocolate and butter; take off heat and add powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.
Spread on top of mixture.
Chill at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Pour in pecans.
Mix together pudding, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Place rolls in pan.
Pour pudding mixture over rolls.
Pour on melted butter.
Cover and let rise for 7 hours or overnight.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for about 30 minutes.
Let cool for 2 to 3 minutes only.
Remove from pan carefully.
Make glaze from milk, confectioners sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Pour over cake.

title: welsh tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar, stir in vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder. Then add eggs and currants.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown beef.
Put everything, except corn, in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 4 hours.
Add corn during last hour.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Combine zucchini, onions and green pepper in large roaster pan.
Salt and garlic.
Stir.
Add 3 trays ice cubes.
Mix through.
Cover and let stand 3 hours.
Combine vinegar, sugar, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed and cloves in Dutch oven and bring to boil.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Use 1/4 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: chicken lush
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cover with buttered crumbs and/or slivered almonds.
Bake in a buttered casserole 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: date muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add dates and beat well.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin tins and bake in moderate oven until golden brown.

title: mandarin orange chiffon pie
directions: In double boiler, mix gelatin, sugar and egg yolks.
Stir in rind and juices (including that from can).
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly 5 minutes, or until thickened.
Beat egg whites in separate bowl until fairly stiff, then add 1/2 cup sugar gradually and beat until stiff.
Fold into egg mixture. Add about 12 to 16 segments of orange.
Turn into pie shell. Garnish with remaining segments and chill.
Yields 6 servings.

title: britt's cocoa mix
directions: Mix milk, cream substitute, Nestles Quik and powdered sugar in large bowl.
Store in airtight jars until ready to use.
Mix 3 tablespoons of mix to 1 glass/cup of milk.
Two recipes make 17 small jars.
Good for gifts.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Pour uncooked rice into large baking pan.
Place chicken on rice.
Mix soups, dry soup mix, water and sherry.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: teriyaki beef kabobs
directions: Combine brown sugar, soy sauce, lemon juice, oil, ginger and garlic.
Stir in beef.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours. Stir meat often.
Thread meat and pineapple alternately on skewers just before broiling or grilling.
Grill approximately 14 minutes, basting occasionally and turning once.
Chicken could be substituted.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Make rice and set aside.
Salt and pepper chicken. Spread rice in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish. Spread 1/2 each of cream of mushroom and chicken soup on top of rice. Add 1/2 package of dry onion soup mix to top of rice.
Place chicken on top of rice. Spread the remaining soups on top of chicken, then the remaining dry onion soup on top.
Pour the milk slowly on top. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry crumble squares
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and eggs.
Grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch baking pan and pat cake mixture into bottom of pan. Top with pie filling.
Combine frosting mix and remaining margarine and sprinkle over cherries.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pans) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: greek beans
directions: Cook beans with bacon and drippings until tender.
Salt to taste.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper in olive oil.
Add this mixture and the tomatoes to beans and let simmer for 1 hour.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup chopped nuts and bananas. Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake springs back when touched. Cool in pans. Cool completely. Spread frosting between layers, on top and sides of cake. Sprinkle top with 1 cup chopped nuts.

title: egg rolls(joe's recipe)
directions: Mix the ground chuck, sherry, cornstarch, pepper, sugar, water and brown gravy mix.
Put 2 tablespoons of oil in wok over medium heat.
Add salt and ginger, then celery and onions; cook about 3 minutes, then add ground chuck mixture to wok.
Stir continuously and break up meat as cooking.
When meat turns brown, put the mixture through a colander or strainer, reserving the drained liquid in a pan.
Spread the meat mixture out flat and let cool. Return the reserved liquid from the meat mixture to the wok and cook the cabbage over medium-high heat until soft.
Mix cabbage with flour and set aside to cool.
Both the meat mixture and the cabbage may be stored in the refrigerator until ready to make egg rolls.
Mix the cabbage, meat mixture and bean sprouts together; crush bean sprouts lightly by hand.

Place about 1/3 cup of egg roll mixture in the center of an egg roll skin and fold like an envelope; moisten the tip and fold over to seal the egg roll. Heat the quart of oil in the wok at high heat for 4 to 5 minutes. Cook egg rolls about 4 at a time until golden brown.
Dip up and drain on a "Tempura" rack or on paper towels.
Keep warm in a 200° oven on a rack until ready to serve.
Serve with dipping sauces. Recipe yields about 24 egg rolls.

title: edible aquarium
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups ice and water.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
If mixture is still thin, refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Pour thickened gelatin into 4 clear dessert dishes; suspend gummy fish in gelatin.
Refrigerate until set, about 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Combine all vegetables in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, oil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight, stirring several times. Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes in a 450° oven until done. Cut potatoes in half and hollow out most of the
potato. Sprinkle diced onion, shredded cheese and bacon bits over hollowed potato skins and return to oven under broiler until cheese is melted. Serve while hot.
Sour cream and/or butter can be added. You can also add other ingredients to suit your taste.

title: betty's egg rolls
directions: Fry ground beef until brown; remove grease.
Combine with cabbage, carrots, onion and raisins.
Add soy sauce while stirring vegetables with meat.
Add dash of salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Cool in a colander to drain fat.
Wrap in lumpia wrappers.
Rub egg whites to seal.
Fry in cooking oil until brown. Makes 25 egg rolls.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Chop green onions.
Fry hamburger meat and onions over low heat until brown.
Remove fat.
Add other ingredients and simmer until warm.
Spoon over hamburger buns.

title: vegetarian soup
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients in oil 5 minutes over medium heat in Dutch oven.
Add squash and water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add greens, beans and tomatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes longer.
Increase heat to boiling.
Add pasta; cook about 10 minutes until pasta is tender.
Add parsley and garlic; simmer 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat at medium speed on mixer all ingredients, except graham crackers and oleo, for 30 minutes.
While beating, roll out graham crackers and oleo (crumble).
Mix and line sides and bottom of spring-form pan.
Add filling and cook in 300° oven for 35 minutes. Take out; turn oven to 450°.
Add 1 pint sour cream mixed with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over cake and put back in oven for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs.

title: mexican skillet
directions: Cook onion and sausage in a skillet over medium heat until onions are tender, but not brown.
Drain.
Add water, rice, salt, seasoning mix and beans.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover tightly and simmer at least 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes or until most of liquid is absorbed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: almond cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place foil baking liners in 12 muffin pan cups.
In large bowl, mix cheese until smooth and beat in eggs, sugar, milk, flour, lemon peel and extract until well blended.
Spoon into cups.
Arrange almonds on cupcakes.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Cool on wire racks.
Spoon jam into center of each cooled cupcake.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in saucepan.
Add milk, egg yolks and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: witch's brew
directions: Mix everything together in a big jug.
While you stir, chant in a deep voice:
"Andy-dandy fiddle foo; Happy Yappy witch's brew."

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix in bowl sugar, cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Mix in separate bowl the pudding and milk.
Cool baked layer. Add cream cheese layer and let settle.
Add pudding layer and let settle.
Add remaining 1/2 container of Cool Whip on top.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Saute onions until opaque.
Add beef and brown.
Add the rest of the ingredients except the flour.
Cook covered 1 1/2 hours on low heat.
When done salt and pepper to taste.
Thicken with flour mixed in cold water.
Serve over broad noodles.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Rub in margarine.
Add buttermilk and mix to a dough.
Place dough on a floured board and knead into a round shape.
Place in a greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Cut a cross right through the dough.
Bake in a 380° oven for 55 minutes or when a skewer comes out clean.

title: scalloped tomatoes made with home-canned tomatoes
directions: Spread toast with 2 tablespoons butter; sprinkle with garlic salt and cut into cubes.
Combine tomatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Place cubes in greased casserole dish.
Add tomatoes. Pour remaining melted butter over top.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: peking shrimp
directions: Combine corn syrup, water, soy sauce, sherry or wine, cornstarch, garlic and ginger; set aside.
Heat oil to medium-low temperature in large frying pan.
Add shrimp and cook, stirring occasionally, about 3 minutes.
Add sauce, tomatoes and peppers and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring gently.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring to boil and boil 1 minute the white sugar, cocoa, vanilla and milk.
Add Mother's oats and peanut butter, stirring until oats and peanut butter are mixed together.
Drop on wax paper with a teaspoon.
Cookies should set up in 1/2 hour.

title: new orleans roast pork
directions: Parboil pork in a large pot with liquid ingredients to cover. Increase apple juice or broth if needed.
Add garlic, cayenne, salt, bay leaves, 1/2 cup green pepper strips and 1/2 cup onions. Cook at a slow boil for 1 to 2 hours.
Remove from liquid and let pork cool.
Slice and place in roasting pan.
Add more dry seasoning to taste and remaining green pepper and onions.
Cover and roast until thoroughly done, not dry.

title: pasta surprise(variations allow you to "surprise" the kids!)
directions: Crush and chop garlic and dice onion and green pepper; saute over low heat in oil until translucent and limp.
Add ground turkey and brown slowly over low heat.
When turkey is cooked through, add tomatoes, salt, pepper, oregano and basil.
If desired, add mushrooms.
Simmer over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ground beef grand style
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain and set aside.
Combine cream cheese, soup, and milk; add salt, catsup, and olives.
Mix well with cooked beef and onions.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Place biscuits on top and return to oven for 10 more minutes or until biscuits are done. Serves 4-6.

title: rice and mushrooms
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Add 1 cup of uncooked rice and 1/2 large onion (chopped).
Cook until rice is golden brown.
Add 1 can of beef consomme and 1 can of water to mixture.
Stir well and add 1 can of sliced mushrooms, drained.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour in 2-quart casserole and cover.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.
Remove cover and bake additional 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with any meat or fish dishes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fettuccine with vegetables
directions: Steam carrots, zucchini, corn and green beans until tender; put aside to cool.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and set aside to cool.
Using blender or food processor, puree cottage cheese until smooth.
Blend in skim milk, basil and parsley.
Combine vegetables and pasta.
Pour sauce over vegetables and pasta; mix thoroughly.
Serve at room temperature. Serves 6.

title: soap bubbles
directions: Mix all together very slowly.
Use straws to blow out bubbles into the air.

title: cheese ball
directions: Add dressing mix, a little at a time, to the cream cheese. Add ham and mix. Place into a bowl lined with plastic wrap.
Chill well. Remove from bowl and remove plastic wrap. Wet hands and shape into a ball. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: spicy baked beans(for a group)
directions: Drain beans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spray dish with Pam.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: cheese roll
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Grind the remaining ingredients, except lemon juice.
Combine all and make into rolls, small or large.
Roll in paprika on wax paper.

title: velveeta microwave fudge
directions: Melt cheese, margarine and cocoa together in microwave. Gradually add sugar.
As mixture cools, re-melt in microwave (nuts optional).
May look grainey when spreading.
Have faith, it smooths as it cools.
Rich and simple!
Yields 6 pounds.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Saute in large kettle bacon and onion.
Add liquor from cans of seafood, potatoes and water.
Cook about 10 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Just before serving, add clams or other seafood, 2 cups milk, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix crabmeat, eggs, chopped celery and mayonnaise well. Chill.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, milk and one package of soup mix.
Make into balls.
Cook until brown.
Drain grease.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until light and fluffy in a medium bowl.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk, stir until well mixed.
Blend in lemon juice & vanilla.
Turn into crust.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut
in shortening.
Add water and shape dough into ball.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough out to fit
9-inch
pie
pan.
Combine
remaining	ingredients except pecans.
Mix well.	Pour
into
unbaked pie shell.	Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon christmas cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and extract (flour, fruit and nuts); beat batter 2 minutes before adding fruit and nuts; mix well.
Bake in tube pan 30 minutes at 300°; reduce heat to 200° and bake for 15 minutes. Serves 20.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Sprinkle chops with salt, coat with flour.
Brown chops on both sides in hot Crisco.
Drain excess fat; add pineapple juice concentrate, the 3/4 c.
water, sugar, lemon juice and spices.
Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes. Combine cornstarch and cold water; add to chops.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens.
Top each chop with pineapple slice; cook for 5 minutes more.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: one pot dinner(makes a big hit - especially with the men.)
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain off fat and put beef in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions; drain off fat.
Add bacon, onions and remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Stir together well.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 6 hours.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: In 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, toss rhubarb with 3 tablespoons sugar.
In medium bowl, combine oats, brown sugar and cornstarch.
With pastry blender or two knives, cut in margarine until coarse crumbs form.
Stir in walnuts.
Spoon evenly over rhubarb.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until rhubarb is tender.
If desired, serve warm with whipped topping.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Lightly grease two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Place chicken pieces in pans and set aside.
In a large deep pot, mix 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup with 2 cans of water and place on low heat.
Pour in wild rice and Success rice; mix well.
Pour mixture over chicken in pans.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water.
Drain, cool, and then peel. Mash in large bowl with butter, milk, and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.
Saute beef until browned, stirring to keep meat crumbled.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, parsley, tomato paste, worcestershire sauce, and gravy.
Mix well.
Add peas and cook about 5 minutes.
Spread potatoes evenly over meat.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes until top is crispy brown.

title: gwen's appetizer pinwheels
directions: Combine cream cheese, onions, garlic, mayo and olives, mix well.
Spread cream cheese mixture on each tortilla, layer ham on top.
Roll tightly.
Wrap each roll in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 1/2 in. slices, save end pieces to sample before serving.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Roll out dough on 15 x 10-inch baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes (until brown).
Mix everything but the veggies and spread on top of cooled dough.
Top with veggies and refrigerate, then slice into small squares and serve.
(Everyone loves this recipe.)

title: layer dip
directions: Serve with corn chips or nacho chips

title: glorified pickles
directions: Slice pickles or cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Mix in gallon or large container.	In pan, mix sugar, vinegar and pickling salt.
Heat until hot, about 5 minutes.
Pour mix over pickles; mix well.	Let set for 10 minutes.
Put in containers. Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 months.
Very crisp.

title: swedish green potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, peel and mash.
Add cream, sugar, butter, salt and pepper.
Beat until fluffy.
Add chives, dill, and spinach.
Beat again.
Taste for personal seasonings.
Add reserved liquid, if needed.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and mayonnaise in a large mixing bowl.
Put drained fruit, whipped cream and cheese in mixture.
Stir all together well and chill overnight.

title: hummus
directions: Process first 7 ingredients.
Add beans and blend until pureed and mix smooth.

title: easy doughnuts
directions: Take one biscuit and using a thimble or anything round, cut out the center of the biscuit.
Take the center out of the thimble and put the center and the biscuit in grease.
Cook until brown.
Then take the powdered sugar and mix with a small amount of milk or water.
Glaze the doughnuts and enjoy.

title: marinated steak
directions: Marinate steaks with remaining ingredients in an airtight container or plastic bag for 24 hours, turning occasionally. Drain and grill steak to desired doneness.

title: baked onion delight
directions: In large 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole, place alternate layers of thinly sliced onion rings, crushed potato chips and grated cheese.
Mix soup and milk together.
Pour over layers and sprinkle pepper on top.
Bake at 350° until done.
Recipe can be divided in half.
Bake time 40 minutes.
Leftovers can be frozen and reheated in the microwave.

title: yogurt deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and set whites aside.
In a small bowl, mash yolks.
Blend in the next 8 ingredients.
Refill whites using about 1 tablespoon yolk mixture for each.
Sprinkle paprika on top of eggs, if desired.
Yield:
1 dozen.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 1 1/2 or 2 hours.

title: cherry crunch
directions: In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spread cherry pie filling in bottom of pan.
Cover with crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Cut up oleo over cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Generously butter a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cut bread into 1-inch slices.
Arrange in single layer over bottom of prepared dish.
Beat the eggs, milk, sugar, salt and vanilla in large bowl until mixed.
Pour over bread; cover with foil.
Refrigerate. Uncover; dot with butter pieces.
Bake, uncovered,
at 350° for 50 minutes, until bread is puffy and lightly browned.
Serve with your favorite syrup or honey.

title: crock-pot corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove and save.
Saute potatoes and onion 5 minutes in bacon drippings. Drain well. Combine all in a crock-pot. Stir well. Cook on low 4 to 7 hours.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Bake angel food cake and break into small pieces.
Place in large bowl and sprinkle with jelly mix (dry, as it comes out of the box) and stir to coat the pieces of cake.
Add thawed strawberries and mix well.
In another bowl, mix the pudding mixes with the 3 cups of milk; beat until thick.
Alternate layers of strawberry cake, pudding and Cool Whip in trifle dish or clear bowl.

title: sourdough starter and bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water, then feed it 1 cup warm water, sugar and potato flakes.
Let stand all day, then refrigerate 2 to 5 days.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Stir 2 cups boiling water into jello; add partially frozen berries to jello.
Tear the angel food cake into bite size pieces; stir into jello mixture.
Spread in a glass pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with fine nuts.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon in baking dish. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Serve with crackers.

title: white peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, mix margarine, sugar and evaporated milk together and bring to a boil.
Boil for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into a lightly greased (margarine) 8 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Cool before cutting.
Serves 16.

title: key lime cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. While still warm, drizzle with 1/2 cup Key lime juice and 2 cups powdered sugar.
Mix together and drizzle over cake.

title: cheese grits souffle
directions: Add salt to boiling water and cook grits, covered, over low heat until done (15 to 25 minutes).
Stir in cheeses, butter, eggs, milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Pour into buttered 3-quart casserole and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: apple roll
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour and shortening until crumbly.
Stir in milk and work dough.
Work and knead until firm enough to roll out into a rectangle.
Put apples and cinnamon on dough and roll up.
Cut like cinnamon rolls.
Place in pan over melted oleo.
Boil sugar and water together.
Pour sugar syrup over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: mountain berry pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Stir in berries.
Add water and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat just to boiling.
Pour in prepared pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Top with a lattice or full crust (cut slits).
Brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden.

title: tropical fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit salad, reserving 1/4 c. juice.
In a bowl, combine yogurt, honey and reserved juice.
Fold in fruit salad, apple, strawberries and grapes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: date pecan candy roll
directions: Combine sugar, cream, syrup and butter in saucepan.
Boil until it reaches 238° or until it forms soft ball when dropped in cold water.

title: avocado dip
directions: Cream avocado and cream cheese in bowl.
Add mayo to desired consistency.
Add lemon juice, onion salt and garlic salt.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: smoked trout or salmon
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Soak fish fillets in brine for 8 hours or more.
Smoke 4 to 8 hours, depending on thickness of fish.
Do not overcook or will be dry.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift again with salt and baking powder. Add corn meal.
Combine eggs, milk, syrup and shortening; add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in greased pan 9 x 9-inch in hot oven, 400°, for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender, drain.
Add tuna, soup, milk and peas.
Mix and pour into greased casserole.
Top with soft bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in next 4 ingredients. Heat until it gets bubbly.
Pour in casserole.
Put biscuits on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Wrap a bundle (about 10 to 15) green beans in 1/2 slice of bacon. Secure with a toothpick or overlap. Place bundles in baking dish and season with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Make a glaze of melted margarine and brown sugar.
Pour over beans. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove and cover for the
last 5 to 10 minutes of baking to brown.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Slowly add milk and vanilla. Continue to beat.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Top with canned strawberries, blueberries or fresh fruit.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients and let set until firm.
Beat cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla and sugar and spread on jello. Top with chopped nuts.
Enjoy!
Serves 12.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Put all ingredients except almonds in prepared casserole. Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: creamed chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken until done, remove from bones and cut in bite-size pieces.
Put in saucepan and add soup (dilute if the chicken is large).
Heat through.
Serve over rice or plain if rice is not liked.
Makes 5 to 6 good servings with an average size chicken.

title: turkey-fruit salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, celery seed, salt and pepper in bowl; blend well.
Add turkey, celery, grapes and apples; mix well.

title: salmon spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except parsley, in a large bowl. Mix well.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: linda's favorite beef tip roast
directions: Combine last 3 ingredients and rub evenly over roast.
Place roast, fat side up, on rack in an open pan. Roast in a slow oven at 325°, uncovered. Do not add water!
Cook 35 to 40 minutes per pound.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes before slicing.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine mustard, oil, vinegar and honey in blender.
Stir in poppy seed and onion.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with an electric beater and pour into a graham cracker or chocolate crust.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: mixed nut bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like a pie crust and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from the oven and pour a bag or can of mixed nuts over the crust.
While the crust is cooking, heat the last 3 ingredients slowly until blended.
(Do not boil.)
Drizzle over the crust and nuts and bake at 350° for 10 more minutes.

title: chocolate lovers pie
directions: Beat eggs and add cocoa, sugar, vanilla, milk, butter and salt. Mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until set.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving.
Top with whipped cream.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon.
Line a greased baking dish (8 x 12 x 2-inch) with chipped beef.
Place chicken breast over beef.
Combine soup and sour cream; pour over chicken breasts.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, bake, uncovered, at 275° for 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 8.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a large glass bowl place lettuce, then layers of celery, onion, pepper and peas.
Spread mayonnaise to the edges of the bowl, sealing all.
Sprinkle sugar, then layer bacon and cheese. Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate until serving. May be prepared a day ahead of serving.

title: rocky road ice cream
directions: Mix frosting mix, whipping cream and milk. Stir in marshmallows and pecans. Pour into ice cream freezer.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute onions, peppers; add hamburger.
When brown add remaining ingredients.
Cook down (low flame), 15 to 20 minutes. Makes about 12 (3 ounce) servings.

title: vegetable pizza with oat bran crust
directions: Combine 1 cup oat bran, flour and baking powder.
Add milk and oil and mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 425°. Lightly spray round pizza pan with vegetable oil cooking spray or oil lightly.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon oat bran.
With lightly oiled fingers, pat dough out evenly.
Shape edges to form rim. Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Spread sauce evenly over partially baked crust.
Top with vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese and oregano. Bake an additional 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into wedges.

title: pacific coast bake
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Stir in rice and salmon.
Add combined mayonnaise and egg; mix lightly.
Layer half the salmon mixture, Parmesan cheese and broccoli in 1-quart casserole; cover with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with broccoli. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Continue baking until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: penny's chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in the top of a double boiler.
Add milk; cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add some of the hot mixture to the beaten eggs.
Add this egg and chocolate mixture to the original mix.
Return to heat; cook for 3 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; mix well.
Pour mixture into a baked 9-inch pie shell. Use egg whites to make a meringue.
Put on top of pie.
Bake until golden brown at 400° (approximately 10 minutes).

title: sour cream pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add wet ingredients.
Pour on hot griddle.
Cook until edges are cooked and air bubbles are forming on top.

title: chili
directions: Cook hamburger, onions, salt and pepper until done, then add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Cook slow for 1 hour.

title: fruit ade
directions: Cook sugar and water for
minutes;	cool; add fruit juices and vanilla.
Makes 1
1/2 quarts.	Add leftover juices of cherry, pineapple, peach or other fruit.

title: honey-glazed acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half.
Remove seeds; place cut side down in shallow pan.
Add 1/2-inch of hot water to pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until almost tender.
Turn cut side up.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: In a large sauce pan cook rhubarb in water for 20 minutes. Gradually add sugar and jello to cooked rhubarb.
Stir will to make sure sugar and jello dissolve.
Refrigerate.
Us as needed.

title: baked taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until brown. Drain. Stir in seasoning mix. Spoon into plate.
Beat Bisquick, milk and eggs with wire whisk until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake about 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake an additional 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Garnish with tomatoes, olives and sour cream, if desired.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; drain and set aside.
Brown meat; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Drain excess fat.
Mix cooked meat with cottage cheese and spaghetti sauce.
In a casserole dish, layer half of the meat mixture.
Place noodles on top and then half of the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbly.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs lightly.
Blend in milk.
Combine sugar and tapioca; stir into egg mixture.
Place bottom pastry in a pie plate; add the rhubarb.
Pour egg mixture over rhubarb.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top pastry.
Make slits in top for steam to escape.
If desired, brush pastry with light cream.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes longer, or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar, if desired.
Cool on a wire rack.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: butterscotch nibbles
directions: In large saucepan over low heat, melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter, stirring frequently.
Stir in cereal until pieces are coated.
Stir in chocolate morsels just until combined but not melted.
Spread on waxed paper lined tray.
Chill 30 minutes or until coating is set.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 9 cups.

title: tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer until thick and lemony. Gradually add sugar.
While beating, add milk and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients together and fold into egg mixture by hand.
Blend ingredients well, then pour into greased and floured 13 x 15-inch pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Spread peanut butter over hot cake.
When cool, cover with melted chocolate or chocolate frosting.

title: fusilli salad with snow peas
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and rinse under cold water.
Set aside.

title: macaroni & beef(skillet)
directions: Lightly brown meat in Wesson oil in skillet, add onion, green pepper, and cook until soft.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper, worcestershire sauce, and macaroni.
cover and simmer 25 minutes or until macaroni is done.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter over medium heat.
Stir in pecans and cook 10 to 15 minutes, until pecans are browned.
Remove from heat and stir in 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cool to room temperature.

title: quick beef and pasta casserole
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Do not overcook. Rinse and drain.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil and 1 tablespoon margarine in large nonstick frying pan on medium-high heat.
Saute onions until translucent, then remove.
Add remaining oil and margarine to pan.
Crumble ground beef into pan and brown evenly.
Drain tomatoes, reserving juice from one can.
Coarsely chop tomatoes. Add onions, tomatoes, basil, thyme, parsley and reserved tomato liquid to pan.
Mix well and bring to a simmer; add pasta, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: halibut jardiniere(microwave method)
directions: Melt butter in a small dish in microwave.
Mix in salt and minced onions.
Spoon over steaks.
Cover and heat 2 minutes on High power (rotate after 1 minute).
Spoon zucchini and tomatoes over steaks.
Cover; heat 1 minute on High.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Heat 1 minute on High or until steaks flake easily.
Do not overcook!

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at about 350° to 400° until done.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Grate half the lemon rind and mix with the juice from half a lemon with the sugar.
Place in pan with the cherries.
Dissolve the cornstarch in the juice from the cherries; add to the pan and heat gently until a thick sauce has formed.
Add the cinnamon.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Cut biscuits in half.
Roll each sausage in 1/2 biscuit.
Bake at 400° until biscuits brown, approximately 15 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water, set aside to cool.
In casserole dish, pour in Jell-O, then add pineapple.
Mix mayonnaise and Cool Whip; set aside.
Put mandarin oranges over Jell-O mixture, then add the mayonnaise and Cool Whip mixture.
Refrigerate overnight or all day.
Grate the cheese over top before serving.

title: puppy chow
directions: Put 8 c. of Rice Chex into a bowl. Melt together 1 c. margarine, 1 c. chocolate chips, 1/2 c. peanut butter. Pour Over Rice Chex.

title: yellow tomato preserves
directions: Cook tomatoes in water and half the sugar for 5 minutes. Simmer 2 hours.
Then add remaining sugar and spices.
Cook at 225°
for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Over low heat, bring to a simmer.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend for 1/2 minute or until ice cubes are crushed.
Serve immediately.

title: apricot bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Let cool.
Add rest of ingredients. Put into 2 greased bread tins.
I prefer nuts to All-Bran, but All-Bran could be substituted.

title: chicken "n" noodles
directions: Cut up chicken; save the broth.
Put noodles in broth; bring to a boil.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer until noodles are done.

title: cheddar skins
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°. Wash and wrap the potatoes in aluminum foil. Pierce each potato with a fork and bake for 1 hour. Remove the foil from the potatoes and cut them in half lengthwise. With a spoon, scoop out 1/4 to 1/2 of each potato. Use the potato insides in another recipe. Sprinkle the cheese evenly over the potatoes. Add the bacon. Bake until the cheese melts. Serve with sour cream if desired.

title: buttermilk raisin pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and lemon juice; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Beat egg yolks until thick; stir in a little of the hot mixture, then pour back into hot mixture and cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and stir in raisins and butter.
Cool slightly, then pour into baked 8-inch pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar gradually.
Swirl meringue over pie filling.
Toast meringue.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Drain well and place in a warm serving dish large enough for tossing.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Sprinkle pudding mix over Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Add pineapple and juice, marshmallows and nuts.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Make and bake like other biscuits, keeping dough soft.

title: caramel crunch apple pie
directions: Layer the apples and caramel topping in the uncooked crust. Mix the flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in the butter until coarse crumbs form.
Mix the nuts with the crumb mixture and sprinkle on top of the apples and sauce.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Good served hot or cold.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sour cream and Cool Whip.
Add pudding, then add milk and stir until well mixed.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
Top with crushed wafers.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: three-week cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onions, pepper and sugar.
Mix oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt.
Bring to a hard boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and stir until well-mixed.
Store in refrigerator in air-tight container.
Let stand at least 3 days.
Flavor improves with age.
Will keep refrigerated for 1 month.

title: warm german-style potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; cool. Remove skins of potatoes and slice. Cut bacon in small pieces and saute until crisp. Remove bacon from fat and place on potatoes. Add flour to bacon fat and then sugar and vinegar. Cook until slightly thickened. Add onion, green pepper, celery, salt and pepper to the potatoes. Pour hot mixture over the potatoes; mix well. Salad can be kept warm in a very low oven. Garnish with sliced hard-cooked eggs. Makes 8 servings.

title: mexicali chicken
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat, cook chicken in cooking spray until no longer pink, about 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand about 5 minutes before serving.
Garnish with optional ingredients; sprinkle with cheese.
Serve and enjoy!

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole, except melted oleo. Pour oleo over all; mix well.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking (room temperature). Keep covered and bake 1 hour.
Stir before serving.
Bake at 350°. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sour cream spice cake
directions: In a bowl blend eggs, sour cream and sugar.
Add sifted dry ingredients; beat until smooth.
Drop in paper cups in a muffin pan and bake in moderate 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 20 cupcakes or 1 large square loaf cake.
Frost with Brown Sugar Frosting.

title: baked bread pudding with apples
directions: Toast bread and cut into cubes.
Put into buttered casserole and cover with hot milk and melted butter.
Let soak for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients except brown sugar. Combine with bread and pour brown sugar over the top.
Bake in a 300° oven for 40 minutes.

title: lemon pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Set aside 1/4 cup jello mixture.
Pour remaining jello in 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Stir in pineapple.
Lay banana slices in rows.
Chill until firm.
Place the remaining jello and whipped topping in a narrow bowl.
Beat on high speed 1 minute.
Set aside in airtight container at room temperature.
Spread on chilled jello and chill for few minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Use one cup less milk in mixing vanilla pudding (sour cream makes up for this).
Use Cool Whip in pudding mix or on top of pudding, whichever you prefer.
Stack: vanilla wafers, one-half of pudding mix, bananas, rest of pudding, then Cool Whip, if you do not mix Cool Whip with other ingredients.
Chill.

title: herb steak butter
directions: Combine butter, Worcestershire and anchovy paste in blender or food processor and mix until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and process until evenly distributed through butter.

title: bean hot dish
directions: Mix browned beef and cooked bacon with rest of ingredients. Bake
in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: basic beer bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Spread in 2 small loaf pans (greased).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: Blend sugar, salt, milk and egg yolks in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture comes to a boil. Cool.
Add vanilla and whipping cream, without whipping. Freeze according to directions on freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Add flour, soda and buttermilk. Then add vanilla and stir in bananas and pecans.
Put in greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: Heat syrup and sugar over medium heat only until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth. Mix in rice cereal.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch buttered pan.
Cut into squares when thoroughly cooled.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients
together
well.
Refrigerate for 3 days, kneading once each day.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine the ingredients and form into 1 1/2 to 2-inch balls. Brown in skillet; put in 2-quart casserole.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese.
Chill.
Dip strawberries, watermelon, grapes, apples or pineapple into the dip and enjoy.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Stir together butter, graham crackers and pecans.
Press over bottom of buttered 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan and refrigerate.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Prepare bacon in skillet over medium heat; drain and crumble. In large stockpot, combine potato patties, water and bouillon granules.
Cover and place over medium-low heat until patties are thawed and crumbled.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients in order listed.
Stir until ingredients are well blended.
Cover and cook over low heat about 20 minutes or until carrots are tender and soup is hot.
Do not allow soup to boil.
Makes 14 (1 cup) servings.

title: coal miner's stew
directions: Peel potatoes and carrots and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Chop onion.
Put vegetables in 3-quart pot.
Add salt, pepper, paprika and bay leaves.
Cover with water.
Cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes.
Add sausage and cook until vegetables and sausage are done, about 10 minutes more.
With a fork, mash one or two pieces of potato against side of pan to thicken the stew.

title: easy brownies
directions: Combine cocoa and soda.
Blend in 1/3 cup oil.
Add boiling water and stir until thickened.
Add sugar, eggs and remaining oil.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla, salt and nuts (if desired).
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan (may sprinkle chocolate chips over top, if desired).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cracker crumbs and 1/3 cup sugar. Stir in the melted butter.
Put in a
9 x 13-inch baking dish. Beat the 2 eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Pour over crust and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown around the edges.
Beat pumpkin, egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, milk, salt and cinnamon.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes until slightly thickened.
Sprinkle gelatin in cold water. Add to pumpkin mixture and cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar until stiff and glossy. Gently fold beaten egg whites into pumpkin mixture.
Pour over baked mixture and refrigerate. Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: skillet barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in frypan.
Pour catsup and Pepsi over chicken. Cook (simmer) for 1 hour.

title: crabmeat "goop"
directions: Mix
cream
cheese,
lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mayonnaise, grated onion and garlic salt with a mixer.
Spread on shallow plate.
Cover with 1/2 bottle chili sauce.	Sprinkle
with crabmeat.	Sprinkle with parsley on top.
Spread on crackers.

title: rice krispy snacks
directions: Place marshmallows and butter in microwave-safe bowl and microwave for 1 to 2 minutes or until butter is melted and marshmallows are soft.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over combined cereal and gumdrops.
Mix until cereal is completely covered with marshmallow mixture.
Put into greased 2-quart oblong dish.
Press smooth and let cool.
Cut into squares or form into 1-inch balls. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.
(Easier to form balls if you put oil on hands.)

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Heat broiler.
Season the roast with the pepper.
Place the meat on the broiler pan rack and broil about 4 inches from the heat, turning until brown on all sides, about 10 minutes.
Reduce the oven temperature to 325°.

title: baked scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place shrimp in large roasting pan. In medium saucepan, melt butter; add pepper and garlic.
Stir in lemon juice and salad dressing.
Pour mixture over shrimp and bake, covered, for 45 minutes.
Stir once or twice while cooking. Pour into large bowl.
Serve with French bread to dip in the butter sauce.
You won't want to waste a drop.

title: ella's swedish meat balls
directions: Beat egg; pour warm milk over bread.
Mix butter, sugar and spices together.
Add meat; mix well.
Add to egg and bread.
Roll in meat balls.
Brown in 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix flour, salt, pepper, water and light cream.
Pour over meat balls in casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: honey bear brownies
directions: Cream
butter
in
small mixing bowl; blend in honey or syrup and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, cocoa and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour
into
a greased 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
Bake at 350°	for
to 30 minutes or until brownies begin to pull
away
from
edge
of pan.	Cool. Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix ingredients in glass jar or container.
Cover loosely; let stand 24 hours at room temperature.
Refrigerate 3 to 5 days.
The fourth day, feed it with 3/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons potato flakes and 1 cup warm water.
Stir; keep at room temperature 24 hours.
Use 1 cup starter to make bread.
Refrigerate remaining batter until next feeding.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and vanilla together.
Add eggs and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Sift and add to other ingredients the flour, soda and salt.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork (crisscross).
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: liver pate
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve on crackers or breads.

title: tony's tortilla roll
directions: Mix all together and press on tortillas.
Roll and slice. Serve and enjoy.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Dip corn tortillas in reserved chicken broth and line a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Put layer of chicken, Cheddar cheese, heated soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes
and slices of Mozzarella cheese. Repeat until all ingredients
are used.
Top with sliced black olives. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade shake 'n bake
directions: Combine ingredients; this will keep, sealed, on the shelf. Use as any shake 'n bake.
Enough for 6 pounds of chicken.

title: lemon cake
directions: Put cake mix in bowl.
Add apricot nectar and oil.
Beat 2 to 4 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat 2 minutes as you add eggs.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Pour icing on cake while warm.

title: peanut butter honey dip
directions: Put some peanut butter in a bowl.
Drizzle about half the amount of honey on it and stir it together until blended.
Dip apple slices, carrot sticks or other vegetables or fruit pieces in it.

title: quick baked beans
directions: *A homemade relish such as a cucumber relish or garden relish is best.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all together and cook for 1 hour or until thick.
Keep stirring so you don't burn.
Take bay leaves out.
Pour into hot, clean jars and seal.
This sauce can be frozen.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Cook sour cream and sugar to 223°.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans.
Pour onto waxed paper and spread apart to dry.
(Great to serve during the holidays.)

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add egg, milk and shortening.
Beat until smooth.
Dip apples in batter and fry in deep hot shortening about 4 minutes or until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve with maple syrup or a sprinkle of confectioners sugar.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old-fashioned sweet potato biscuits
directions: Blend and mix all ingredients until smooth.
Turn out on a lightly floured board.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on a greased cookie pan.
Bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes.

title: pasta with peas and ham
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add peas and ham; heat through.
Cook and drain pasta; add to peas and ham.
Pour in whipping cream; heat until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese and nutmeg.
Serve immediately.

title: pafford's bean dip
directions: Blend everything except the grated cheese in a blender. Pour into baking dish
and
bake
at
350° until grated cheese topping is melted.
Garnish
with
sour
cream and green onion pieces. Add a whole
black
olive
or 3.
Serve with Tostitos for dipping.

title: hop scotch crunchies
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water the butterscotch morsels and peanut butter. Remove from heat. Stir in chow mein noodles and marshmallows. Drop by spoon onto wax paper lined cookie sheet. Chill until set.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Measure margarine into 3-quart saucepan.
Melt by a low heat. Add marshmallows and cook, stirring until marshmallows have melted and are very syrupy.
Remove from heat, add Rice Krispies.
Stir until very well coated.
Spread warm mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, using waxed paper or greased or buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place hash browns in a 3-quart casserole.
Mix 1 stick oleo, soup, cheese, sour cream, salt and onions.
Pour over hash browns. Top with crushed corn flakes.
Drizzle 1 stick oleo over top. Bake at 350°, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Serves 15.

title: halushki(cabbage and noodles)
directions: Dice and saute onion in margarine or butter.
Shred cabbage; add to onions and saute.
Add pepper to taste.
Add a little bit of water in the pan with the cabbage and onion and cover.
Simmer until the cabbage is soft.
Stir occasionally, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
