Remove from heat and combine with the cooked noodles. Mix and serve.

title: cider doughnuts
directions: Mix dry ingredients, Mix liquid ingredients in a blender. Combine dry and wet ingredients together. Pat with flour until not sticky. Chill 1 hour. Roll out dough and cut, deep fry 2 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add apples.
Add dry ingredients and oil.
Add nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in greased pan.

title: l & h inn salad dressing
directions: Mix well and
shake before using.
Mixes well in blender. Makes 1 quart.

title: teriyaki potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes, scrub thoroughly with a vegetable brush.
Cut tiny new potatoes into quarters or medium potatoes into 1 inch pieces.
Place potatoes in 1 1/2 quart microwave-save casserole. Add margarine or butter, teriyaki sauce, garlic salt, Italian seasoning, black pepper, and red pepper.
Toss to combine.
Cover and microcook on 100% power (HIGH) for 12 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring twice during cooking.
Stir before serving.
Garnish with snipped rosemary and serve with sour cream if desired.
Makes 5 side dish servings.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender while holding the lid on. Blend 30 seconds.

title: bill's famous cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and sugar together by kneading or vigorously stirring.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.
You may add more sugar, vinegar or seasoning if needed after removing from refrigerator for individual taste.

title: roast leg of lamb with oyster stuffing
directions: Wipe lamb with all natural paper towels.
Heat oven to 325°. In a large bowl, combine oysters with 1/4 cup of their juice, the scallions, dill, bread cubes and egg.
Turn lamb upside down on the counter.
Stuff with oyster mixture.
Tie together at several places so that the leg of lamb completely surrounds filling. Place lamb, fat side up, in a shallow roasting pan; pour 1/2 cup wine over top.
Sprinkle with salt and pressed garlic.
Roast 2 1/2 hours.
Remove roast to warm platter.
Discard string.
Add flour to remaining wine.
Spoon off fat from drippings in pan. Stir in wine and flour mixture.
Cook, stirring, until thickened. Serve gravy with lamb.
Makes 8 servings.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour, shortening and salt, cutting together with a pastry knife.
In a one-cup measuring cup, add egg, vinegar and enough cold water to make one cup.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll on heavily floured surface.
Makes 4 to 6 pie crusts.
Excellent for pot pies or dessert pies.

title: fried green tomato sandwiches
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients in a shallow bowl. Dip tomato slices in egg and dredge in breadcrumb mixture. Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Cook tomatoes in batches 2 minutes on each side or until golden. Drain on a wire rack over paper towels. Layer lettuce, onion, fried green tomatoes and bacon evenly on bottom half of each roll. Drizzle evenly with dressing. Cover with tops of rolls. Serve immediately.

title: tapioca cream
directions: Mix egg yolk with small amount of milk; add tapioca, sugar, salt and remaining milk.
Cook in double boiler over boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring frequently, or bring quickly to a boil over direct heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; mixture will be thin.
Fold hot mixture into egg whites.
Cool slightly.
Add vanilla.
Chill thoroughly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: indian tacos
directions: Brown meat and onions together; drain fat.
Add salt and pepper, tomato sauce and other seasonings.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Thaw bread enough to cut into 8 pieces.
Oil hands and stretch each piece into saucer shape.
Deep fry to golden brown.
Ladle meat and bean sauce on bread.
Top with lettuce, cheese, onion, tomato and picante sauce.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cover peas with boiling water for 1 minute; drain.
Mix all ingredients (but cheese and potato chips).
Pour into a greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese and potato chips.
Bake 10 minutes at 450° or 20 minutes at 400°.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In a bowl, whisk together flour and salt. Whisk in 1 cup seltzer, whisking until smooth, and let batter stand 10 minutes. If necessary, thin batter with enough remaining seltzer to reach consistency of crepe batter.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 1 cup of sauce.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for an additional 35 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; grease a 10 x 15 or 9 x 13-inch pan. In a large bowl, beat brown sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add molasses, vanilla and eggs; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Stir in oats, flour, baking soda and salt; blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips (and, if desired, peanut butter chips and chopped nuts).
Spread in pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (until light golden brown).
Cool slightly and cut into bars.

title: pork and rice
directions: Spread rice in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Add mushrooms, soup and hot water.
Add pork; cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: sour cherry salad
directions: Make jello by package directions, using 1 cup boiling water, cold juices and water to make 1 cup.
Add all other ingredients. Chill.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Drain and crumble. Simmer celery, green pepper and onion in bacon drippings until done.
Add peas, tomatoes and bacon.
Season with salt and pepper. Simmer about 20 minutes.

title: versatile cookie mix peanut butter cookies
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: zucchini relish(low sodium)
directions: Mix the zucchini, onions and peppers and let stand overnight. Drain and rinse in cold water.
Drain again and pour into large kettle.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Process in hot water bath for 20 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 pints.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Grease pan and put batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy green pea salad
directions: Drain the sweet peas and add the grated onion.
Stir in enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Serve chilled.

title: dixie's party punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Mix all ingredients together. Place in 5-quart ice cream bucket to freeze.
Take out of freezer 3 hours before using.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Place torn bread in bottom of shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Pour the melted butter on top.
Microwave the onion and celery one minute on High.
Add tomatoes, brown sugar, onion and celery to casserole.
Stir gently.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: layered mexican bean dip
directions: Mix refried beans and chilies; spread on a 12-inch serving plate to within 3 inches of edge.
Layer guacamole, salsa, sour cream and cheese over bean mixture.
Garnish with tomato, olives and scallions, if desired.
Serve as a dip with Triscuit wafers.

title: homemade ice cube ice cream
directions: Pour into ice tray and freeze.
Stick fork in cube and eat.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine granulated sugar, 1 stick melted butter and graham cracker crumbs; mix well.
Line a 9 x 12-inch dish or pan with crumbs.
Combine 2 sticks butter, 1 teaspoon extract and 2 cups powdered sugar; beat with electric mixer 15 minutes on medium speed.
Pour over crumbs.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt, butter and water together.
Add eggs and another cup of flour.
Stir well.
Add as much of the remaining 3 cups of flour as needed.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Layer as follows:
bean dip, ground beef, green chilies, taco sauce and grated cheese. Microwave until cheese is melted.
Warm tortillas.
Roll mixture in tortilla and garnish with sour cream, if desired.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat cookie dough into ungreased 14 inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 - 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
In a mixing bowl, beat cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread over the crust.
Arrange fruit on top until pleasing in appearance.
In a saucepan, bring sugar, orange juice, water, lemon juice, cornstarch and salt to a boil, stirring constantly for 2 minutes, or until thickened.
Cool, then brush over fruit.
Store in refrigerator.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together over medium heat; drain well.
Cut cheese into small pieces.
Cut tomatoes into small pieces.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir and turn on low heat.
Heat for 3 or 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel, boil and mash eggplants.
Saute onion and peppers in oleo, about 6 minutes.
Add raw rice; cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and broth; season with salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; add to eggplant.
Cook in casserole dish for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bread crumbs just before removing from oven.

title: clam dip
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add clams with juice.
Add parsley, garlic powder, onion and oregano to skillet.
Stir well. Add enough bread crumbs until medium pastry consistency.

title: blintz souffle
directions: With whisk, combine sour cream, orange juice, eggs, margarine, flour, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon until well blended, scraping sides occasionally.
Set aside.
For filling, beat cottage cheese, egg yolks, sugar, vanilla and cream cheese in small bowl until well blended.
Pour half of batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drop filling by spoonfuls over the batter; spread evenly. Pour remaining batter on top of filling.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 to 65 minutes or until puffed light golden brown.
Serve hot, topped with sour cream and apricot preserves or fresh fruit and powdered sugar.
Serves 12.

title: paradise pie
directions: Beat egg whites with pinch of salt and vanilla.
Mix cracker crumbs with pecans and baking powder.
To egg whites, fold in sugar.
Fold dry ingredients into egg white mixture.
Bake in ungreased pie pan at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Add vanilla ice cream or whipped cream to the pie shell.
Freeze for a few hours if desired.

title: oven baked red snapper
directions: Cook the onion rings in the olive oil over medium heat until tender-crisp (about 5 minutes).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, layer onion rings, red snapper and sliced mushrooms.
Combine in a small bowl the tomatoes, pepper, white wine, salt and garlic powder.
Spoon tomato mixture evenly over fish and vegetables. Sprinkle with the oregano leaves and chopped parsley.
Bake at 350° until fish flakes easily at thickest part, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: basic baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare Creamettes macaroni according to package directions. Drain.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine. Stir in flour, mustard and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens slightly (mixture should coat spoon).
Remove from heat.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Sift the sugar, flour, baking powder, and salt together.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Combine filling ingredients and beat until well blended.
Pour filling into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: italian soft crabs
directions: Saute minced garlic in olive
oil and butter.
Sprinkle soft crabs with garlic powder and
saute.
Add
2 ounces white wine; cook until crabs are reddish.
When
done, place on foil covered cookie sheet.
Cover with
foil.
Place
in
300° oven for 5 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: liberty fruit cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Add dry ingredients and blend until smooth.
Stir in fruit, nuts and dates.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen cookies.

title: alma davis' sandwich spread
directions: Mix tomatoes, 1 teaspoon salt, peppers and vinegar.
Boil 10 minutes.
Drain off the liquid.
Mix flour, sugar, eggs, 1 teaspoon salt, mustard and sour cream.
Cook until thick.
Add to vegetables and heat to boiling point.
Seal hot.
Makes about 3 pints.

title: broccoli and cheese soup(ultra low-fat)
directions: In medium saucepan, simmer chicken broth, broccoli, celery and onion flakes 10 minutes.
Add evaporated milk, Molly McButter and sour cream.
Simmer 1 minute.
Do not boil.
Break cheese into small pieces and drop into soup.
Stir and simmer until cheese melts.
Add black pepper.
Serve.
Recipe makes 4 servings.

title: imperial deviled crab
directions: Melt butter in sauce pan.
Add flour, stir until smooth.
Add all remaining ingredients, except crumbs and shells.
Mix well and put into crab shells.
Sprinkle with crumbs and bake in hot oven for 10 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple; save liquid.
Measure and add enough water to make a cup.
Add together mixture; stir in drained blueberries and pineapple.
Pour into a 2-quart flat pan.
Cover and put in refrigerator until firm.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Spread over congealed salad.
Sprinkle with chopped pecan pieces.

title: brisket soup
directions: Cut brisket into bite-sized pieces.
In a large Dutch oven, heat oil and brown meat on all sides. Add water, salt, pepper and carrots.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars and flour.
Beat in eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Fold in pecans.
Spoon into 12 pie tarts (unbaked).
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: crowd pleasin' macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Rinse with cold water; drain.

title: wasso
directions: Boil together for 10 minutes water and sugar.
Remove from heat and add cloves, cinnamon sticks and allspice.
Cool for 30 minutes. Add orange juice, lemonade and apple juice.
Chill.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: bleu cheese muffins
directions: Grease muffin tins.
Cut each biscuit into 3 pieces and place 3 pieces in each muffin cup.
Melt butter and Bleu cheese.
Pour mixture equally over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Invert pan on rack for 3 to 5 minutes and serve hot.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl. Mix until dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Stir in other ingredients.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or until firm.

title: salad dressing
directions: Cook vinegar, salad oil and sugar for about 2 minutes; cool. Combine remaining ingredients in a blender.
Add the cooled mixture.
Store in a glass jar in the refrigerator.

title: beef stew with gravy
directions: Brown meat in a little oil. Fill cooking pan 1/3 full with water. Add browned meat, bouillon or consomm and seasoning mix. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and let simmer for 2 hours or until tender. Add mixed vegetables, potatoes and carrots. Cook 30 to 40 minutes more or until tender.

title: spicy sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, eggs, spices, milk and 3/4 cup coconut with sweet potatoes; mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining coconut on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook, crumble and drain sausage. Mix together the Bisquick, sausage, salt and grated cheese.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Yields 80.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: aunt sarah's chicken casserole
directions: Crush Ritz crackers, medium fine.
Pour on butter and mix. In another bowl, combine soup, sour cream, and chicken stock and mix well.
Line casserole dish with 1/3 of cracker mixture.
Add layer of chicken and soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with last 1/3 of cracker mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza pie
directions: Spread soft sugar cookie dough over pizza pan and bake.
Let cool.
Cover baked cookie dough with vanilla pudding.
Arrange any fruit you want on top of pudding.
Mix a preserve you like with a little water until you can spread it on top of fruit.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: ham and sweet potato casserole
directions: Brown ham slightly in 1 tablespoon butter.
Whip potatoes until smooth and combine with beaten eggs, milk, lemon juice and salt; again whip thoroughly.
Mix with the browned ham and drippings, and turn into a buttered casserole.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yields 5 servings.

title: basil chicken
directions: In a large plastic food bag, combine first 7 ingredients; add chicken.
Close.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 325°. Place chicken in single layer with marinade in roasting pan. Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake 30 minutes or until juice runs clear when pierced.
Skim fat from drippings.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Beat the eggs, then add the oil and beat again.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Place broiler halves over the fire, turning every 5 to 10 minutes.
The chicken should be basted at each turning.
Cooking time is about 1 hour.
Leftover sauce can be placed in a glass jar and stored in refrigerator for several weeks.
Serves 100.

title: very fast fruitcake
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, apricot nectar, 1/4 cup apricot brandy and oil.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes or until mixture is smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Fold in fruits and nuts.
Turn into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool 15 minutes in pan.

title: angel food jello dish
directions: Make Jell-O according to directions.
Add pineapple.
Let set until thickened (about 1 1/2 hours).
Tear small chunks off of cake; put in a layer in a large bowl (use glass bowl so layers show).
Spoon Jell-O over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over Jell-O.
Repeat until all is used up, ending with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.

title: butterflake rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.	Cream sugar and shortening.
Add
water,
eggs
and
yeast.
Stir in flour and salt.
Let	stand
in
refrigerator overnight.
Roll out thin, like
jelly roll.
Spread with melted butter and roll up.
Cut roll
in
1 1/2-inch pieces.
Dip in butter and place buttered side
up in muffin tins.
Let rise 3 hours.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: favorite corn dogs
directions: Combine
flour,
meal, onion, sugar and mustard in bowl. Mix milk and egg in a small bowl.
Stir into corn meal mixture. Pat frankfurters dry; insert popsicle stick in each.
Dip into batter. Deep fry
in
to
400° oil for 2 to 3 minutes or until brown, turning once;
drain on paper towels.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: cheese bread
directions: Slice bread lengthwise.
Melt butter.
Add mayonnaise and cheese and mix.
Spread mixture on bread.
Broil until cheese is light brown (5 to 6 minutes).
Slice and serve.

title: sausage and pintos
directions: Fry sausage until brown on all sides.
Drain off the fat.
Add onion, pepper, pinto beans and tomato sauce. Stir to blend. Simmer until onion and pepper are tender.
Serve hot with corn bread.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Wash tomatoes; cut into quarters and slice very thin.
Stir in raisins, lemon juice, rind, vinegar and salt.
Blend flour with sugar and spices.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over bottom of pastry lined pan.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar mixture.
Fold rest of sugar mixture into tomatoes and flour in pan.
Dot with butter. Cover with top crust.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 50 minutes longer.

title: kolaches
directions: Mix first four ingredients well and let rise to double size. Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and let stand about 15 to 20 minutes.
Then mix real well; the more the dough is mixed, the smoother and easier to handle.
Dust top well with flour and set in warm place to rise double again.

title: whole wheat batter bread
directions: Measure into medium mixing bowl the warm water and yeast. Stir to dissolve.
Mix in large bowl the whole wheat flour, white flour and salt.
Add to 1/2 of flour mixture the shortening, honey and yeast.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour and blend with spoon until smooth.
Cover with waxed paper; let rise until about double in size, 30 to 60 minutes.
Stir down batter by beating about 25 strokes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop from teaspoon on buttered pan and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Vary the spices and discover a different taste each time you bake these.

title: strawberry bavarian
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in sour cream with wire whisk.
Add ice cream in 1-inch cubes and stir until melted. Add strawberries and lemon juice, stirring until blended.
Pour mixture into 12 (6 ounce) parfait glasses and chill.
Just before serving, combine whipping cream and powdered sugar; beat at medium speed.
Top each parfait glass and garnish with mint.

title: white trash
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot (except confectioners sugar) and cook over low heat stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in 7 cups Crispex cereal.
Stir until well coated and spread onto wax paper.
Coat with confectioners sugar.
Let cool, then break apart and store in air tight container.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Cook rhubarb into sauce.
Add sugar to sweeten.
Add enough cornstarch to thicken and 1 egg to each pie.
Pour into pie shell. Top with meringue.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add onion.
Beat egg; add milk and add to dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot fat (375°).
Fry until golden brown and serve hot with fried fish. Makes about 48 small balls.

title: ham salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water and heat.
Combine remainder of ingredients and add to gelatin mixture.
Chill.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream Wesson oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients; mix with oil, eggs and flour mixture.
Add nuts and apples.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mama's orange sliced cake
directions: Sift flour with salt. Combine candy, dates, nuts and coconut with 1/2 cup of flour and mix well. Cream butter with sugar and add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine soda and buttermilk. Add alternately with flour and blend well. Pour into a greased tube pan. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours. Place a pan of water under the cake.

title: seven thing bean soup
directions: Mix all together and cook until beans are tender.

title: gert's golden punch
directions: Stir water and sugar, bring to a boil and cool.
Mix all juices and fruit into this syrup and freeze in plastic containers. When ready to serve, remove to punch bowl and add ginger ale or 7-Up.
It is best for mixture not to thaw too much; it tastes better a bit thick and requires no ice.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt butter and combine with graham crackers.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 340° oven for 20 minutes.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Drain the fruit.
Mix all ingredients well and chill before serving.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan. Spread graham cracker crumbs evenly over melted butter.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Spread with chocolate and butterscotch chips. Drizzle condensed milk evenly over entire mixture.
Top with nuts. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: everyday potato soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Cook potatoes in salted water in saucepan until tender. Drain. Simmer carrots, onion and celery in a small amount of water in saucepan until carrots are tender. Drain.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients.
Cook until heated through.
Do not boil.

title: chicken breasts marsala
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper in a medium bowl.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese in small bowl. Spread on aluminum foil.
Dip chicken breasts in beaten eggs, then coat with bread crumb mixture.
Press mixture into chicken with the palms of your hands.
Let chicken stand 10 to 15 minutes. Melt butter with oil in a large skillet.
When butter foams, add chicken breasts.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until chicken has a golden crust.
Add Marsala.
Cover skillet and reduce heat.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender. If sauce looks too dry, add a little more Marsala.
Turn chicken several times during cooking.
Place on a warm platter and spoon the sauce over the chicken.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put potatoes in the bottom of a casserole dish. In a separate bowl, mix the soup, sour cream, onion, cheese, salt and pepper. Top with crushed corn flakes and drizzle with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green tomato mince
directions: Simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Seal while hot.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: apricot brandy slush
directions: Heat sugar and water until dissolved.
Steep the tea bags in boiling water for half an hour.
Add to the sugar mixture.
Add lemonade and orange juice.
Mix well. Add brandy.
Mix in a gallon container.
Freeze and stir from time to time.
Put 2 tablespoons in short glasses and add cold 7-Up, Teem or Fresca.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Mix dry ingredients along with coffee to sugar and molasses mixture.
Drop dough from spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet 3-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat butter with 1 cup sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each.
Beat in flour mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts and lemon peel.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.

title: wedgies
directions: Amounts of ingredients vary according to taste and how much is needed.

title: egg salad sandwich spread
directions: Chop ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Spread on open-faced sandwich.
Use rye bread, French or strips of bread. Makes about 3 1/2 cups of spread.
An extra egg can be added for volume.

title: old tyme pound cake(makes 20 servings.  prep time:  20 minutes.)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

Add vanilla flavoring. Add flour gradually, beating well. Grease or spray Bundt cake pan. Spoon mixture into pan. Mixture will be thick and won't pour easily. Bake in preheated 350° oven for about an hour.
Cool 30 to 45 minutes before removing from pan.

title: tea cake
directions: Cream sugar with butter, eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add enough plain flour to make a good stiff dough.
Roll out and cut. Cook in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and shape into a ball.
Sprinkle with pecans. Serve with crackers.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together at medium speed until blended.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Yields 2 cups.

title: white pizza
directions: Spread Ricotta cheese over pizza crust to desired thickness, then add shredded Mozzarella cheese, garlic, oregano and parsley. Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: veggie dip
directions: Precook fresh beets.
Remove skins by putting in cold water. Slice and put in jars.

title: my son-in-law's favorite pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream margarine.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg yolks, flour, milk, lemon rind, juice and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form.
Fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Yield:
one 10-inch pie.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Combine broth, pepper, salt, carrot, onion, celery, mushrooms, parsley and apple.
Simmer 1 hour.
Remove solids from broth and puree.
Cook the 1/2 cup chopped onion in margarine until soft. Stir in flour and curry powder.
Gradually add broth and pureed solids and stir.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in rice and half and half; heat through.
(May thin if desired with more half and half.) Serves 6.

title: chocolate pecan pie bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour mixture over melted butter and add fruit on top.
Do Not Stir!
Bake at 350 degrees until crust is golden brown.
This makes a real good peach cobbler, just sprinkle some cinnamon and sugar on it when it comes out of the oven.

title: pork chop supper
directions: Brown pork chops in a small amount of shortening in skillet. Remove pork chops, setting aside.
Add rice and onion.
Cook until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Add 2 cups of water and bouillon and bring to a boil.
Stir in apple.
Turn into casserole, arranging pork chops on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake for 20 minutes longer or until pork chops are tender.
Yields 4 servings, about 440 calories each.

title: sheet cake
directions: Boil shortening and water; cool down some.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add cocoa and salt to shortening and water.
Add sugar and butter; when ingredients are about room temperature, add eggs, flour, soda, vanilla, milk and cinnamon.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 20 minutes at 400°.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Pour graham cracker crumbs in a large mixing bowl.
Heat can of milk and pour onto crumbs.
Mix well.
Cut 1 jar of cherries in small chunks and add to mixture.
Add 1/2 box of raisins, 1/2 bag of coconut and 2 bags of pecan pieces.
Mix all these ingredients thoroughly.

title: seafood stir-fry linguine
directions: Cook onions, garlic, olive oil and margarine for 30 seconds. Add 1/2 of scallop/shrimp mixture, parsley, basil and red pepper. Cook and stir for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove mixture from pan.
Cook remaining half of shrimp/scallop mixture.
Return all to pan and add snow peas and tomatoes.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Place in large bowl over linguine.
Sprinkle fresh Parmesan on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place vegetables in a casserole dish.
Melt cheese and 1/2 stick of butter together.
Pour over vegetables.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Pour remaining 1/2 stick of melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Grease a large round pizza pan.
Open crescent rolls and place them around the pan in a pinwheel shape.
Bake in a 375° oven until golden brown.

title: three layer carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325.
Oil 3 - 8-inch cake pans.
(or large 9 x 13-inch pan).
Set out 1/2 c. butter, 8 oz. cream cheese to soften (for frosting).
Put pineapple in sieve to drain.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add sugars and beat till light and fluffy.
Add oil and mix well with whisk.
Put in the dry ingredients and beat till smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour batter into pans. Bake for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted in enter of cake.
Cool and frost.

title: cucumber marinade
directions: Combine ingredients, except cucumbers, and pour over cucumbers.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Combine white sugar with cinnamon.
Put sugar mixture into bag.
Put cut up biscuits in bag, a few at a time, and shake.
Melt butter and brown sugar, then boil 1 minute.
In a Bundt pan, place one layer of coated biscuits. Sprinkle with melted butter and brown sugar and a few dabs of butter.
Repeat layers. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Let stand for 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: company squash casserole
directions: Melt oleo in large skillet.
Mix in herb seasoning.
Pour half of the crumbs into 13 x 9 casserole dish.
Pour soup and squash mixture over the crumbs.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until good and hot.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Season and flour pork chops.
Fry until done.
Chop into cubes.
Pour off all grease from frying pan.
Saute onions in dipping.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Let simmer 5 minutes; turn off fire. Add cooked rice, meat, soy sauce and sweet and sour sauce.
Cover for 15 to 20 minutes, then serve.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Debone and set aside.
Cook the vermicelli noodles in the broth.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
When spaghetti is done, add all ingredients.
Make a large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave shrimp scampi
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, put butter, garlic, lemon and parsley.
Microwave on High 2 1/2 minutes until butter melts.
Add shrimp.
Toss.
Cover and microwave on High 2 1/2 minutes.
Toss again.
Cover and microwave on High another 2 1/2 minutes until all shrimp are pink.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Combine in a bowl and then spoon in pie shell and chill. Sprinkle with coconut and chocolate sprinkles.

title: betty brown's beanie weanies
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add all ingredients except tortillas. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Fry the tortillas until crisp.
Top with the meat mixture.
Cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream, olives or anything you like can be used as a garnish.

title: rachel's meat loaf
directions: Add bread crumbs, milk and egg into a bowl.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Add meat, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into loaf and spread ketchup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: gnocchi
directions: Place mashed potatoes, eggs and salt in bowl and mix thoroughly.
Add 1 1/2 cups of flour and mix well.
Place dough on floured board and add rest of flour.
Knead 3 to 4 minutes.
(If dough becomes too sticky, sprinkle the board with more flour.)

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats for 20 minutes.
Cream oleo and sugars. Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chex treat
directions: Melt coating in microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Repeat 2 or 3 times until coating mixture is smooth.
Pour over dry mixture, coating evenly.
Spread on waxed paper to dry.
Crumble as it dries.

title: potato balls
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add onion, olives, 1 egg and seasonings.
Let mixture cool.
Form balls into about a half dollar size.
Dip balls into remaining egg that has been beaten, and roll in cracker meal.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, fry in 3/4-inch of very hot oil.
Serve hot with tartar sauce.

title: meat balls
directions: Cook chili sauce and grape jelly; keep stirring.
Make meat balls; pour sauce over.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, crackers, 1/2 the can of tomato sauce, egg and seasoning.
Shape into loaf.
Put into loaf pan.
Combine remaining sauce with 3/4 cup water, 1 teaspoon vinegar, 2 teaspoons brown sugar.
Pour over loaf.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: overnight breakfast
directions: Put ham, cheese and bread in a greased pan.
Mix the eggs, milk, salt and mustard together, then pour over the food in the pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add clams, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste.

title: egg custard
directions: Combine and beat well.
Pour into 8-inch square dish.
Place dish in 13 x 9 x 3-inch baking pan and pour 1-inch of hot water in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: hot maple wings
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter.
Add maple syrup.
Cook until warm.
Add hot sauce.
Dip wing pieces in sauce; lay on baking sheet in single layer.
Bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: tortellini alfredo
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add cream and simmer until warm. Add pepper and 3 tablespoons grated cheese.
Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Add tortellini to cream mixture. Serve sprinkled with remaining cheese.

title: blackened seasoning for meat
directions: Coat meat (steak, chicken, fish, etc.) with butter.
Roll in seasoning mix.
Fry meat in very hot iron skillet.

title: scallops jerez
directions: Melt butter and saute scallops for 5 to 6 minutes.
Turn scallops and add lemon juice, soy sauce, sherry and dill.
Cook covered over low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove scallops and cook down sauce until thickened.
Pour over scallops.
Serve in warm dishes with lemon wedges.

title: mac & cheese
directions: Boil and drain macaroni, add sour cream, egg and velveeta cheese.
Put in baking dish and layer cheese on top.
Bake @
325 degrees until cheese is melted.

title: stir n bake cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pyrex dish.
Mix all ingredients except fruit; pour mixture over butter and pour fruit over batter.
Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: curried turkey and broccoli
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Saute onion just until soft. Stir in flour, salt, pepper and curry powder.
Heat for 1 minute. Stir in
broth and cream.
Cook, stirring constantly,
for 5 minutes.
Add
tomato
paste
and
cook
minutes longer.
Pour half of sauce into
a
x 9-inch baking dish. Arrange
broccoli along
sides.
Overlap
turkey
slices
down through middle.
Pour remaining
sauce over turkey.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: corn meal muffins
directions: Combine in a medium bowl.
Mix quickly until just blended. Small lumps will bake out.
Pour into well oiled muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 17 to 20 minutes.
Remove muffins from tins immediately and cool on wire racks.
Makes 12 regular sized muffins or 8 jumbo muffins.

title: sweet-sour ribs
directions: Melt shortening and brown ribs until golden.
Lower heat. Combine the rest of the ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover and braise 1 1/2 hours or until tender and ribs are glazed.

title: breast of chicken with honey
directions: Season chicken with seasoning, salt and pepper.
In a jar, place all other ingredients.
Shake well.
Place chicken in a single layer in a shallow baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Pour sauce over chicken and bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours or until tender at 325°.

title: hot tomato catsup
directions: Use ripe tomatoes; peel and cut up tomatoes and onions.
Put in pan; cook about 1 hour.
Then add pepper, sugar, vinegar, peppers, cinnamon and salt.
Cook another hour to an hour and a half.
Then pour in pint jars and seal while hot.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Chop onions and shrimp.
Fluff rice with a fork.
Lightly beat eggs.
Stir together broth, soy sauce, and pepper in a small bowl.
In skillet or wok, heat oil on medium-high heat.
Do not allow it to reach smoking point.
Stir fry eggs about 30 seconds. Add onion and stirfry for about 2 minutes.
Add shrimp and peas. Cook until heated thoroughly.
Add rice and cook another 3 minutes.
Stir in soy sauce.
Mixture yields 5 servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually stir in pumpkin, lemon juice and sugar.
Mix flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking powder, ginger and salt in separate bowl.
Fold this into pumpkin batter.
Spread mixture on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Turn out on a towel, which has been sprinkled with powdered sugar. Roll towel and cake up together longways and let cool completely. Unroll and spread with filling.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Precook peppers 5 minutes.
Sprinkle insides with salt.
Brown meat with onion.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Stir in blended tomatoes, rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Stuff peppers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes until very firm.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
When starting to thicken, fold in cream, marshmallows, pineapple and cottage cheese.
Set aside to thicken.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Saute in oil the onion and garlic.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a blender or food processor and blend.

title: sugar-free pineapple pie
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press into bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes; cool. In a bowl, combine pudding mix (dry) and sour cream; mix well. Stir in pineapple and sweetener. Spread into crust. Chill at least 3 hours. Yield: 8 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut in colander for 15 minutes.
Cut into 1 inch pieces with scissors.
Place in large mixing bowl; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Store covered in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: rhubarb pizza
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Cut in margarine.
Beat egg lightly and add milk.
Mix well with the flour mixture.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Chop cabbage; add salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Chop bell pepper and carrot and add to cabbage.
Bring to a boil, the vinegar, water, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Pour boiling hot over cabbage.
Stir well and let cool.
Pack in containers and freeze.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Place one spoonful of mixture into tortilla and roll (tortillas may be softened by cutting a slit in the plastic package and microwaving for approximately 20 to 25 seconds).
Place in 11 x 14-inch glass dish which has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Cover with remaining mixture and sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover dish with plastic wrap.
Cut several air holes in the wrap and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
